WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:01:41.936 --> 00:01:43.545
We're screwed.

3
00:01:43.646 --> 00:01:45.280
No more free Wi-Fi.

4
00:01:46.716 --> 00:01:47.716
Hey. Ki-Jung!

5
00:01:47.817 --> 00:01:48.884
Yeah?

6
00:01:48.985 --> 00:01:53.055
The lady upstairs
put a password on "iptime".

7
00:01:53.156 --> 00:01:54.890
A password?

8
00:01:54.991 --> 00:01:56.624
Did you try 123456789?

9
00:01:56.768 --> 00:01:57.768
No luck.

10
00:01:57.869 --> 00:01:59.269
Try it in reverse.

11
00:01:59.370 --> 00:02:00.771
I tried that too!

12
00:02:00.872 --> 00:02:05.108
Fuck. then we can't get WhatsApp?

13
00:02:05.209 --> 00:02:06.384
Nothing.

14
00:02:06.961 --> 00:02:09.179
Hey. Kim Ki-taek.

15
00:02:09.714 --> 00:02:13.183
Don't fucking pretend to sleep.
What do you think?

16
00:02:13.718 --> 00:02:19.773
Our phones are shut off.
Now our Wi-Fi is shut off.

17
00:02:20.308 --> 00:02:23.401
What's your plan?

18
00:02:25.688 --> 00:02:26.922
- Ki-woo.
- Yes. Dad?

19
00:02:27.023 --> 00:02:30.950
For Wi-Fi. hold it up high.

20
00:02:32.570 --> 00:02:36.164
Search out every corner.

21
00:02:39.702 --> 00:02:43.755
Damn stink bugs.

22
00:02:44.290 --> 00:02:46.483
Over here! I got it!

23
00:02:46.584 --> 00:02:47.901
Really? You got a signal?

24
00:02:48.002 --> 00:02:49.820
Yeah. see?

25
00:02:49.921 --> 00:02:52.572
This one. "coffeeland 2G".

26
00:02:52.673 --> 00:02:54.658
Did a new cafe open nearby?

27
00:02:54.759 --> 00:02:56.368
Why can't I get it?

28
00:02:56.469 --> 00:02:58.078
Climb up here.

29
00:02:58.179 --> 00:02:59.479
Hey kids.

30
00:02:59.879 --> 00:03:01.873
- Is it working?
- Yeah.

31
00:03:01.974 --> 00:03:04.526
Then check WhatsApp.

32
00:03:05.061 --> 00:03:07.403
Pizza Generation said they'd contact me.

33
00:03:07.939 --> 00:03:09.322
Hold on.

34
00:03:09.857 --> 00:03:12.200
Here it is. Pizza Generation.

35
00:03:15.238 --> 00:03:18.974
Wow! Check this out. guys.

36
00:03:19.075 --> 00:03:22.269
If we go as fast as her.
we can finish all these today.

37
00:03:22.370 --> 00:03:23.603
Then we can get paid.

38
00:03:23.704 --> 00:03:27.173
- She does it standing.
- She's a pro.

39
00:03:27.333 --> 00:03:30.301
What's that? Fumigation?

40
00:03:31.963 --> 00:03:33.447
They still do that kind of thing?

41
00:03:33.548 --> 00:03:34.548
Guess so.

42
00:03:34.549 --> 00:03:35.469
Shut the window.

43
00:03:35.470 --> 00:03:38.028
Leave it open.
We'll get free fumigation.

44
00:03:38.052 --> 00:03:39.744
And get rid of the stink bugs.

45
00:03:39.845 --> 00:03:42.730
Right. too many
stink bugs these days...

46
00:03:44.809 --> 00:03:47.151
God. that smells!

47
00:03:49.689 --> 00:03:51.423
I told you to shut it!

48
00:03:51.524 --> 00:03:53.616
Should I shut it. Dad?

49
00:04:04.453 --> 00:04:06.254
What exactly is the problem?

50
00:04:07.290 --> 00:04:10.108
Take this one as an example.

51
00:04:10.209 --> 00:04:12.552
You call this a straight line?

52
00:04:13.087 --> 00:04:14.946
And why's it folded here?

53
00:04:15.047 --> 00:04:16.698
Why is this sticking out?

54
00:04:16.799 --> 00:04:19.392
You didn't finish folding it.

55
00:04:20.428 --> 00:04:24.206
A quarter of them look like this.

56
00:04:24.307 --> 00:04:26.858
So 1 out of 4 are rejects.

57
00:04:30.021 --> 00:04:33.907
So you're really docking
10% off our pay?

58
00:04:34.233 --> 00:04:37.911
Considering the fail rate.
that's a low penalty. isn't it?

59
00:04:38.779 --> 00:04:42.040
Our pay is so low already!
How can you do this?

60
00:04:44.076 --> 00:04:45.076
Look here.

61
00:04:45.177 --> 00:04:47.979
This is not some minor issue.

62
00:04:48.080 --> 00:04:53.134
You know what one shitty boss
can do to our brand image?

63
00:04:53.544 --> 00:04:56.888
Brand? You can't even
afford a box folder!

64
00:04:57.131 --> 00:04:58.264
What did you say?

65
00:04:59.300 --> 00:05:00.400
Boss.

66
00:05:01.385 --> 00:05:02.696
This is all because
of that guy. right?

67
00:05:02.720 --> 00:05:03.678
What guy?

68
00:05:03.679 --> 00:05:07.541
Your part-time worker.
He's gone AWOL. right?

69
00:05:07.642 --> 00:05:10.752
Just when the Love of God Church
made a huge group order?

70
00:05:10.853 --> 00:05:13.988
How do you know all that?

71
00:05:14.148 --> 00:05:15.715
Who told you?

72
00:05:15.816 --> 00:05:17.801
My sister knows the guy.

73
00:05:17.902 --> 00:05:22.429
He's always been a bit strange.
Got a bad reputation.

74
00:05:22.530 --> 00:05:24.623
Speaking of which. Boss.

75
00:05:25.158 --> 00:05:27.184
We'll accept the 10% penalty.

76
00:05:27.285 --> 00:05:28.346
In return...

77
00:05:28.370 --> 00:05:29.711
In return?

78
00:05:29.871 --> 00:05:32.356
Any thought of hiring
new part-time help.

79
00:05:32.457 --> 00:05:35.842
Sis. we need it.

80
00:05:36.378 --> 00:05:39.805
Ditch the guy you've got now.
Just fire him.

81
00:05:40.590 --> 00:05:43.725
Tomorrow I'll come for
a formal interview. What time?

82
00:05:44.010 --> 00:05:45.352
Wait. hold on a sec.

83
00:05:45.971 --> 00:05:48.230
Let me think about it.

84
00:05:48.765 --> 00:05:52.067
Then for now.
just pay for the boxes.

85
00:05:58.566 --> 00:06:02.035
So we've all gathered here today...

86
00:06:02.320 --> 00:06:05.681
To celebrate the
reconnection of our phones.

87
00:06:05.782 --> 00:06:09.602
and the bountiful Wi-Fi!

88
00:06:09.703 --> 00:06:13.255
That bastard!
So early in the evening!

89
00:06:13.790 --> 00:06:17.484
Why haven't you put up the
'No Urinating' sign?

90
00:06:17.485 --> 00:06:18.435
I told you to!

91
00:06:18.436 --> 00:06:22.823
No. a sign like that
only encourages them.

92
00:06:23.258 --> 00:06:25.034
At least yell at him!

93
00:06:25.135 --> 00:06:26.768
Don't shout.

94
00:06:26.886 --> 00:06:29.021
"Please don't piss!"

95
00:06:30.557 --> 00:06:33.650
Hey. is that Min-hyuk?

96
00:06:34.185 --> 00:06:36.253
Hey mister. that's not a toilet.

97
00:06:36.354 --> 00:06:37.671
That is Min-hyuk.

98
00:06:37.772 --> 00:06:39.840
Hey. punk!

99
00:06:39.941 --> 00:06:43.160
Who are you staring at. asshole?

100
00:06:43.319 --> 00:06:46.830
Come here! You little shit.

101
00:06:48.450 --> 00:06:50.917
Get a fucking grip!

102
00:06:51.953 --> 00:06:53.979
Your friend has spunk!

103
00:06:54.080 --> 00:06:57.149
University students have
real spirit.

104
00:06:57.250 --> 00:06:58.269
Unlike you. big brother.

105
00:06:58.293 --> 00:07:01.695
But is he coming here?
Were you expecting him?

106
00:07:01.796 --> 00:07:02.896
No.

107
00:07:03.006 --> 00:07:04.031
Hello!

108
00:07:04.132 --> 00:07:05.766
Oh hi. Min-hyuk!

109
00:07:05.909 --> 00:07:06.909
Min!

110
00:07:06.910 --> 00:07:07.985
Have you been well. sir?

111
00:07:07.986 --> 00:07:10.679
- Of course.
- Hey. what's the occasion?

112
00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:12.272
I texted you. Didn't you see it?

113
00:07:12.807 --> 00:07:13.874
Sorry. you were eating.

114
00:07:13.975 --> 00:07:15.167
No. we weren't eating.

115
00:07:15.268 --> 00:07:17.544
- How are you. Ki-Jung?
- Fine. you too?

116
00:07:17.645 --> 00:07:20.381
You should've asked to meet up.
Why come all the way here?

117
00:07:20.482 --> 00:07:24.276
Because of this.
It's for you. but it's so heavy.

118
00:07:24.277 --> 00:07:26.578
Really? Put it down here.

119
00:07:28.615 --> 00:07:30.224
Wow. what is that?

120
00:07:30.325 --> 00:07:31.892
When I said I was meeting Ki-woo.

121
00:07:31.993 --> 00:07:35.253
my grandfather insisted
I bring this along.

122
00:07:39.793 --> 00:07:41.968
Is this an artscape stone?

123
00:07:43.087 --> 00:07:44.947
It's also called a zen stone.

124
00:07:45.048 --> 00:07:46.740
Wow. you know these!

125
00:07:46.841 --> 00:07:50.869
My grandpa has collected these
stones since his military days.

126
00:07:50.970 --> 00:07:54.498
Now downstairs. upstairs.
living room. the study...

127
00:07:54.599 --> 00:07:56.583
all filled with these things.

128
00:07:56.684 --> 00:08:00.546
But this stone here is said to
bring material wealth to families...

129
00:08:00.647 --> 00:08:01.988
Min!

130
00:08:02.148 --> 00:08:05.259
This is really symbolic!

131
00:08:05.360 --> 00:08:08.679
For sure!
Truly. this is very timely.

132
00:08:08.680 --> 00:08:09.771
Isn't it?

133
00:08:09.772 --> 00:08:13.825
Please relay our gratitude
to your grandpa.

134
00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:15.919
Food would've been better.

135
00:08:25.713 --> 00:08:28.866
What was that called?
Artscape stone?

136
00:08:28.967 --> 00:08:30.284
You collect those rocks too?

137
00:08:30.385 --> 00:08:35.147
Hey. thanks to that rock. I got to
see your parents. They looked healthy.

138
00:08:36.683 --> 00:08:40.652
They're plenty healthy.
just out of work.

139
00:08:42.772 --> 00:08:45.740
Is Ki-Jung taking lessons
these days?

140
00:08:46.276 --> 00:08:49.327
She can't afford lessons.

141
00:08:57.954 --> 00:08:59.546
She's cute. huh?

142
00:09:00.456 --> 00:09:02.733
Oh. she's the one
you're tutoring?

143
00:09:02.834 --> 00:09:05.277
Park Da-hye.
High school sophomore.

144
00:09:05.378 --> 00:09:08.763
You take over as her English tutor.

145
00:09:09.032 --> 00:09:10.032
What do you mean?

146
00:09:10.133 --> 00:09:12.642
Tutor a rich kid. It pays well.

147
00:09:13.678 --> 00:09:14.787
She's a good kid.

148
00:09:14.888 --> 00:09:18.273
Look after her while
I'm studying abroad.

149
00:09:18.808 --> 00:09:22.169
What about your
university friends?

150
00:09:22.270 --> 00:09:25.864
Why ask a deadbeat like me?

151
00:09:26.399 --> 00:09:27.741
Why do you think?

152
00:09:28.276 --> 00:09:30.385
Just the thought makes me sick.

153
00:09:30.486 --> 00:09:34.640
Those disgusting frat boys
fawning all over Da-hye?

154
00:09:34.741 --> 00:09:37.083
It's revolting.

155
00:09:42.624 --> 00:09:44.090
You into her?

156
00:09:49.130 --> 00:09:51.306
Hey. I'm serious.

157
00:09:52.342 --> 00:09:56.728
When she enters university.
I'll officially ask her out.

158
00:09:56.846 --> 00:09:58.622
Until then. take good care of her.

159
00:09:58.723 --> 00:10:03.235
If it's you.
I can leave in peace.

160
00:10:04.771 --> 00:10:07.447
Thanks for trusting me. but...

161
00:10:07.565 --> 00:10:11.409
Do I have to pretend
to be a college student?

162
00:10:12.946 --> 00:10:15.914
Ki-woo. think about it.

163
00:10:16.449 --> 00:10:19.852
For years including
your military service.

164
00:10:19.953 --> 00:10:22.271
you took the university
entrance exam 4 times.

165
00:10:22.372 --> 00:10:25.423
Grammar. vocabulary.
composition. conversation...

166
00:10:25.959 --> 00:10:27.442
When it comes to English.

167
00:10:27.543 --> 00:10:31.888
you can teach 10 times better than
those drunken college pricks.

168
00:10:33.424 --> 00:10:36.017
- I guess so.
- Sure!

169
00:10:36.177 --> 00:10:39.872
But will they hire me?
I'm not a college student.

170
00:10:39.973 --> 00:10:41.498
Just fake it.

171
00:10:41.599 --> 00:10:45.735
Don't worry. you'll have
my recommendation. plus...

172
00:10:46.271 --> 00:10:49.447
How should I describe the mother...?

173
00:10:51.484 --> 00:10:52.885
She's a bit simple.

174
00:10:52.986 --> 00:10:54.136
Young and simple.

175
00:10:54.237 --> 00:10:55.370
Simple?

176
00:10:55.905 --> 00:10:57.306
What do you mean?

177
00:10:57.407 --> 00:11:01.668
It's all good. I had fun there.

178
00:11:02.187 --> 00:11:03.187
So you agree?

179
00:11:03.288 --> 00:11:05.088
I guess so.

180
00:11:06.124 --> 00:11:10.027
Hey. you said your sister
is very talented.

181
00:11:10.128 --> 00:11:14.323
Good with Photoshop?

182
00:11:14.424 --> 00:11:18.535
With skills like this.
why can't you get into art school?

183
00:11:18.636 --> 00:11:20.270
Wanna die?

184
00:11:22.432 --> 00:11:24.583
Hey. no smoking in here.

185
00:11:24.684 --> 00:11:26.084
Yeah. yeah. Gimme that.

186
00:11:26.185 --> 00:11:27.360
Yeah.

187
00:11:31.691 --> 00:11:34.659
Now the cherry on top...

188
00:11:36.195 --> 00:11:40.599
Wow. does Seoul National University
have a major in document forgery?

189
00:11:40.700 --> 00:11:44.061
Ki-Jung would be top of her class.

190
00:11:44.162 --> 00:11:46.855
Amazing skills. huh?

191
00:11:46.956 --> 00:11:52.469
Our boy's going for a job interview.
Wish him luck.

192
00:11:53.004 --> 00:11:54.104
Son.

193
00:11:55.048 --> 00:11:58.016
I'm proud of you.

194
00:11:58.134 --> 00:11:59.234
Dad.

195
00:12:00.136 --> 00:12:03.372
I don't think of this
as forgery or crime.

196
00:12:03.473 --> 00:12:05.457
Because I'm going to
this university next year.

197
00:12:05.558 --> 00:12:09.044
So you've got a plan!

198
00:12:09.145 --> 00:12:13.323
I just printed out
the document a bit early.

199
00:12:48.475 --> 00:12:49.775
Who is it?

200
00:12:50.310 --> 00:12:52.128
Madame? Good afternoon.

201
00:12:52.229 --> 00:12:54.005
I'm here on Min-hyuk's
recommendation...

202
00:12:54.106 --> 00:12:56.240
Oh. right. Come on in.

203
00:12:57.275 --> 00:12:58.375
Thank you.

204
00:13:30.308 --> 00:13:31.567
Hello!

205
00:13:32.310 --> 00:13:33.711
Hello. Madame.

206
00:13:33.812 --> 00:13:37.239
I just work here. Come this way.

207
00:13:37.774 --> 00:13:39.383
The garden is so nice.

208
00:13:39.484 --> 00:13:41.118
The interior is nice. too.

209
00:13:41.653 --> 00:13:44.938
You know the architect
Nam-goong? He's famous.

210
00:13:45.039 --> 00:13:47.750
He used to live in this house.

211
00:13:49.911 --> 00:13:52.129
He designed it himself.

212
00:13:55.167 --> 00:14:00.137
As you can see.
now it's a family home.

213
00:14:00.672 --> 00:14:01.772
This way.

214
00:14:04.176 --> 00:14:06.543
Please sit here and wait.
I'll bring the madame.

215
00:14:06.644 --> 00:14:07.744
Yes.

216
00:14:19.941 --> 00:14:21.200
Madame.

217
00:14:22.235 --> 00:14:23.452
Madame?

218
00:14:28.950 --> 00:14:30.459
Madame?

219
00:14:33.997 --> 00:14:36.423
He's here.
The tutoring candidate.

220
00:14:39.961 --> 00:14:42.179
I don't care about documents.

221
00:14:42.714 --> 00:14:45.265
Min-hyuk recommended you. after all.

222
00:14:45.967 --> 00:14:52.022
As you know. Min is such
a brilliant person.

223
00:14:52.557 --> 00:14:54.792
Da-hye and I were
quite satisfied with him.

224
00:14:54.893 --> 00:14:58.129
Regardless of her grades.
Know what I mean?

225
00:14:58.230 --> 00:14:59.330
Yes.

226
00:14:59.856 --> 00:15:01.507
Things were very good.

227
00:15:01.608 --> 00:15:08.530
So to be honest. we wanted to stick
with him through high school.

228
00:15:09.366 --> 00:15:12.709
But all of a sudden
he's leaving to study abroad.

229
00:15:14.871 --> 00:15:20.359
So. excuse me for
being blunt. but...

230
00:15:20.460 --> 00:15:25.281
if you're not up to
Min-hyuk's level...

231
00:15:25.382 --> 00:15:27.808
there's really no point.

232
00:15:29.844 --> 00:15:33.581
So anyway.
what I want to say is.

233
00:15:33.682 --> 00:15:39.336
for your first lesson today.
do you mind if I sit in.

234
00:15:39.437 --> 00:15:43.407
I want to see it full time.
how you run your lessons.

235
00:15:45.443 --> 00:15:47.536
Is it okay with you?

236
00:16:15.682 --> 00:16:17.482
You sure about #24?

237
00:16:25.525 --> 00:16:30.137
Da-hye. you solved those later
problems then went back to #24.

238
00:16:30.238 --> 00:16:31.913
Right?

239
00:16:33.450 --> 00:16:34.791
Yes.

240
00:16:42.417 --> 00:16:47.888
If that were the first question
on a real exam. you'd be screwed.

241
00:16:48.423 --> 00:16:52.059
Look at this.
Your pulse is racing.

242
00:16:54.596 --> 00:16:58.023
The heart doesn't lie.

243
00:16:59.267 --> 00:17:02.127
An exam is like
cutting through a jungle.

244
00:17:02.228 --> 00:17:05.072
Lose that momentum
and you're finished.

245
00:17:05.231 --> 00:17:07.591
The answer to #24? I don't care.

246
00:17:07.692 --> 00:17:13.080
Punching through the exam.
dominating it!

247
00:17:13.615 --> 00:17:15.499
That's all I care about.

248
00:17:16.534 --> 00:17:20.253
It's all about spirit.

249
00:17:21.331 --> 00:17:22.714
Spirit.

250
00:17:23.792 --> 00:17:25.217
Understand?

251
00:17:36.262 --> 00:17:39.039
So I'll pay you
this time each month.

252
00:17:39.140 --> 00:17:42.317
3 classes a week.
2 hours each. okay?

253
00:17:43.169 --> 00:17:44.169
As for the amount...

254
00:17:44.270 --> 00:17:48.007
I pay Min-hyuk's rate.
but I added a bit for inflation.

255
00:17:48.108 --> 00:17:49.658
Thank you.

256
00:17:51.194 --> 00:17:53.178
How about a proper introduction?

257
00:17:53.279 --> 00:17:56.206
Da-hye's English tutor.
we'll call him Kevin.

258
00:17:56.825 --> 00:17:58.583
Mr. Kevin!

259
00:17:59.119 --> 00:18:02.479
If you get hungry during
your lesson. just let me know.

260
00:18:02.580 --> 00:18:04.648
If you need anything. ask her.

261
00:18:04.749 --> 00:18:07.342
She knows this house
better than anybody.

262
00:18:07.502 --> 00:18:10.929
Da-song! Watch the head!

263
00:18:11.540 --> 00:18:12.817
I'm sorry. did he startle you?

264
00:18:12.841 --> 00:18:15.284
How cute. His name is Da-song?

265
00:18:15.385 --> 00:18:17.202
Yes. our youngest.

266
