00:34:48.374 --> 00:34:50.191
So instead...

527
00:34:50.292 --> 00:34:55.322
Can you just invent some
harmless excuse to let him go?

528
00:34:55.423 --> 00:34:56.781
Okay sure.

529
00:34:56.882 --> 00:35:00.243
No need to mention
panties or car sex.

530
00:35:00.344 --> 00:35:02.329
We don't need to stoop
to that level. do we?

531
00:35:02.430 --> 00:35:04.439
Surely not!

532
00:35:04.974 --> 00:35:07.834
But what if he goes online and
accuses us of wrongful termination?

533
00:35:07.935 --> 00:35:09.944
Just give him a good severance.

534
00:35:10.479 --> 00:35:13.757
How was Da-song today?

535
00:35:13.858 --> 00:35:15.950
He was fine.

536
00:35:16.485 --> 00:35:18.595
- So class is finished?
- Yes.

537
00:35:18.696 --> 00:35:21.264
Jessica. the last time you came.

538
00:35:21.365 --> 00:35:23.808
our driver gave you a ride. right?

539
00:35:23.909 --> 00:35:24.868
That's right.

540
00:35:24.869 --> 00:35:27.228
This may be an odd question.

541
00:35:27.329 --> 00:35:29.213
but nothing happened then?

542
00:35:29.331 --> 00:35:30.690
No. he was very nice.

543
00:35:30.791 --> 00:35:32.651
I told him to go
to Hyehwa Station.

544
00:35:32.752 --> 00:35:36.029
but he insisted on
driving me home.

545
00:35:36.130 --> 00:35:39.282
That jerk!
He took you home late at night?

546
00:35:39.383 --> 00:35:41.059
To find out where you live?

547
00:35:42.094 --> 00:35:44.371
No. I got off at Hyehwa.

548
00:35:44.472 --> 00:35:46.831
Oh. good. You did very well.

549
00:35:46.932 --> 00:35:48.500
Jessica. nice!

550
00:35:48.601 --> 00:35:50.960
Did something happen with him?

551
00:35:51.061 --> 00:35:56.257
He won't be working for us anymore.
A slightly shameful incident.

552
00:35:56.358 --> 00:35:58.301
What incident?

553
00:35:58.402 --> 00:36:01.370
Oh. enough about that.

554
00:36:02.907 --> 00:36:06.518
But I'm surprised. He was
so gentlemanly and cool.

555
00:36:06.619 --> 00:36:09.938
Jessica. you're too
young and innocent!

556
00:36:10.039 --> 00:36:12.131
You have a lot to learn about people.

557
00:36:13.167 --> 00:36:17.737
At the time we were excited to
have such a young. hip driver.

558
00:36:17.838 --> 00:36:21.032
But isn't an older driver better?

559
00:36:21.133 --> 00:36:25.120
That's true. They drive better.
have better manners.

560
00:36:25.221 --> 00:36:27.872
My uncle had a driver
just like that.

561
00:36:27.973 --> 00:36:32.419
Mr. Kim... He was so
congenial and nice.

562
00:36:32.520 --> 00:36:35.046
I used to call him 'uncle' too
when I was young.

563
00:36:35.147 --> 00:36:37.132
You know a man like that?

564
00:36:37.233 --> 00:36:40.284
Yes. he was so mild-mannered.

565
00:36:40.820 --> 00:36:45.581
Oh. but my uncle
relocated to Chicago.

566
00:36:46.659 --> 00:36:48.852
I wonder if Mr. Kim's free now?

567
00:36:48.953 --> 00:36:52.939
I'm quite interested!
Could I meet him?

568
00:36:53.040 --> 00:36:54.107
Really?

569
00:36:54.208 --> 00:36:56.592
I can't trust people nowadays.

570
00:36:57.127 --> 00:37:00.029
I only trust someone recommended
by a person I know well.

571
00:37:00.130 --> 00:37:04.809
But if you've known him so long.
that is reassuring.

572
00:37:07.388 --> 00:37:09.438
Do you really want to meet him?

573
00:37:09.974 --> 00:37:11.482
I'm deadly serious.

574
00:37:12.017 --> 00:37:15.570
Networking through
trusted referrals seems best.

575
00:37:16.105 --> 00:37:17.321
How should I describe it?

576
00:37:17.481 --> 00:37:18.906
A safety belt of trust?

577
00:37:19.425 --> 00:37:20.502
- This one's different.
- Here.

578
00:37:20.526 --> 00:37:21.192
Oh. right.

579
00:37:21.193 --> 00:37:22.827
And this one.

580
00:37:22.945 --> 00:37:24.471
Looks like a touch screen now.

581
00:37:24.572 --> 00:37:27.474
It's not touch.
it says you have to turn it.

582
00:37:27.575 --> 00:37:29.625
Wow. this thing?

583
00:37:30.060 --> 00:37:31.060
Sir?

584
00:37:31.161 --> 00:37:33.504
Taking our time. are we?

585
00:37:36.102 --> 00:37:37.931
This is a nice car.

586
00:37:40.880 --> 00:37:42.096
Here it is! Come over here.

587
00:37:45.801 --> 00:37:47.351
He's in a meeting now.

588
00:37:52.391 --> 00:37:54.400
Have a seat and wait here.

589
00:38:03.027 --> 00:38:06.495
Hello. nice to meet...

590
00:38:09.617 --> 00:38:11.177
But is it compatible
with mobile phones?

591
00:38:11.201 --> 00:38:17.882
No. that requires
more computing power.

592
00:38:19.001 --> 00:38:23.638
This isn't a test drive.
so don't be nervous.

593
00:38:24.381 --> 00:38:27.433
I was worn out at the office.
so I came out for a bit.

594
00:38:27.968 --> 00:38:29.118
I understand.

595
00:38:29.219 --> 00:38:33.814
Constant chatter. all that bother.
At least the car is peaceful.

596
00:38:36.226 --> 00:38:37.526
Thank you.

597
00:38:38.562 --> 00:38:39.831
You seem to know the roads well?

598
00:38:39.855 --> 00:38:43.174
Anything below the 38th parallel.

599
00:38:43.275 --> 00:38:46.535
It comes naturally
after 30 years behind the wheel.

600
00:38:47.071 --> 00:38:49.705
I respect those who work
in one field for a long time.

601
00:38:49.949 --> 00:38:52.934
Well. to be honest
this is a simple vocation.

602
00:38:53.035 --> 00:38:56.045
But... the head of a household.

603
00:38:56.580 --> 00:38:57.730
the leader of a company?

604
00:38:57.831 --> 00:39:03.344
Or else just a lonely man setting off
on the road each morning...

605
00:39:04.213 --> 00:39:05.972
It's companionship of a sort.

606
00:39:06.131 --> 00:39:09.033
So. that's been my approach
each and every day.

607
00:39:09.134 --> 00:39:11.018
The years sure pass quickly.

608
00:39:14.723 --> 00:39:17.358
Sure enough.
your cornering is excellent.

609
00:39:18.060 --> 00:39:24.424
Well. it may look simple.
but it's fundamental.

610
00:39:24.525 --> 00:39:29.287
She may look sheepish.
but inside. she's a fox.

611
00:39:29.405 --> 00:39:32.498
Sometimes she acts like
she owns the house.

612
00:39:33.017 --> 00:39:34.017
Right.

613
00:39:34.118 --> 00:39:38.605
She's lived there longer
than anyone in that house.

614
00:39:38.706 --> 00:39:42.358
She was housekeeper
to the architect Nam-goong.

615
00:39:42.459 --> 00:39:47.138
but then she stayed on
to work for this family.

616
00:39:47.673 --> 00:39:49.032
When the architect moved out.

617
00:39:49.133 --> 00:39:52.035
he introduced this woman
to Mr. and Mrs. Park.

618
00:39:52.136 --> 00:39:55.479
telling them. "This is a great
housekeeper. you should keep her."

619
00:39:55.597 --> 00:39:58.917
So she survived
the change of ownership.

620
00:39:59.018 --> 00:40:02.069
She won't give up the good job easily.

621
00:40:02.604 --> 00:40:05.740
To extract a woman like that.
we need to prepare well.

622
00:40:07.443 --> 00:40:09.785
Right. we need a plan.

623
00:40:10.821 --> 00:40:14.373
I want some peaches.
I like peaches best.

624
00:40:14.908 --> 00:40:16.017
Why not ask for some?

625
00:40:16.118 --> 00:40:19.879
No peaches at our house.
It's a forbidden fruit.

626
00:40:27.546 --> 00:40:30.406
So according to what
Da-hye told me.

627
00:40:30.507 --> 00:40:35.119
she's got a massively serious
allergy to peaches.

628
00:40:35.220 --> 00:40:38.456
You know that fuzz
on a peach's skin?

629
00:40:38.557 --> 00:40:42.168
If she's anywhere near it.
she gets a full body rash.

630
00:40:42.269 --> 00:40:46.238
has trouble breathing.
asthma. a total meltdown!

631
00:40:50.778 --> 00:40:54.914
No no. there weren't
any peaches anywhere.

632
00:40:56.575 --> 00:40:59.043
That's what I'm saying!

633
00:40:59.286 --> 00:41:01.771
Usually when I get
symptoms like this.

634
00:41:01.872 --> 00:41:05.274
I run to my room
and take my medicine.

635
00:41:05.375 --> 00:41:10.738
but it was so sudden. I panicked
and forgot where I put it!

636
00:41:10.839 --> 00:41:15.868
Madame. this woman
behind me. is that...?

637
00:41:15.969 --> 00:41:17.870
Oh. it's our housekeeper!

638
00:41:17.971 --> 00:41:20.623
So it's true. Oh. how sad.

639
00:41:20.724 --> 00:41:23.710
I wasn't sure if that
was really her.

640
00:41:23.811 --> 00:41:27.571
I've only seen her a couple times
in the living room.

641
00:41:28.107 --> 00:41:30.091
This was in the hospital?

642
00:41:30.192 --> 00:41:34.120
A few days ago I went
for my annual checkup.

643
00:41:34.654 --> 00:41:38.665
I took a selfie for my wife.
and there she was. behind me.

644
00:41:39.158 --> 00:41:41.167
She's talking to someone
on the phone?

645
00:41:41.369 --> 00:41:46.523
I wasn't trying to eavesdrop...

646
00:41:46.624 --> 00:41:48.442
but her words came through clearly!

647
00:41:48.543 --> 00:41:50.277
- So I couldn't help but..
- Cut. cut!

648
00:41:50.378 --> 00:41:53.238
Dad. your emotions are up to here.

649
00:41:53.339 --> 00:41:55.598
Bring them down to about here.

650
00:41:56.134 --> 00:41:58.577
So I couldn't help but overhear.

651
00:41:58.678 --> 00:42:01.438
Keep it focused!

652
00:42:02.974 --> 00:42:05.250
What I'm trying to say is.
it's just that.

653
00:42:05.351 --> 00:42:09.571
her voice was quite loud!

654
00:42:09.730 --> 00:42:13.258
It's all right.
Just tell me. okay?

655
00:42:13.359 --> 00:42:16.178
She said she got
diagnosed with active TB.

656
00:42:16.279 --> 00:42:18.346
and she was shouting
on the phone.

657
00:42:18.447 --> 00:42:21.516
so upset she could
barely control herself!

658
00:42:21.617 --> 00:42:23.935
Tuberculosis? Come on...

659
00:42:24.036 --> 00:42:29.382
It's true. she phoned someone
saying she had Active TB.

660
00:42:29.917 --> 00:42:34.512
Do people still get TB?

661
00:42:34.706 --> 00:42:35.806
Dad...

662
00:42:36.048 --> 00:42:41.036
Back in the day. people used
to buy Christmas Seals. right?

663
00:42:41.137 --> 00:42:42.454
Feels like a bygone era.

664
00:42:42.555 --> 00:42:44.206
But I saw it on the internet.

665
00:42:44.307 --> 00:42:48.126
Korea has the #1 rate of TB
of all the OECD countries.

666
00:42:48.227 --> 00:42:51.755
But she's still working.
as if nothing's wrong.

667
00:42:51.856 --> 00:42:53.799
With a kid like Da-song
in the house.

668
00:42:53.900 --> 00:42:57.177
So you've got a young kid
like Da-song in the house.

669
00:42:57.278 --> 00:43:00.514
and a TB patient is doing dishes.
cooking. spraying spittle...

670
00:43:00.615 --> 00:43:02.248
Stop it. please!

671
00:43:06.537 --> 00:43:08.546
[Dad: Arriving in 3 mins.]

672
00:43:55.086 --> 00:43:59.097
If you get the chance.
this'll be icing on the cake.

673
00:44:29.287 --> 00:44:30.979
[Madame:]

674
00:44:31.080 --> 00:44:34.465
[2nd floor sauna room.]
[Don't let her know.]

675
00:44:44.510 --> 00:44:46.102
- Have a seat.
- Yes.

676
00:44:48.247 --> 00:44:49.247
Mr. Kim.

677
00:44:49.348 --> 00:44:53.418
Please don't tell any of this
to my husband. okay?

678
00:44:53.519 --> 00:44:54.544
I understand.

679
00:44:54.645 --> 00:44:59.324
If he hears I've harbored a
TB patient to our home.

680
00:44:59.483 --> 00:45:02.219
I'll be hanged and quartered!

681
00:45:02.320 --> 00:45:04.221
Don't worry. Madame.

682
00:45:04.322 --> 00:45:07.933
And if I may say one thing

683
00:45:08.034 --> 00:45:11.336
I have no feelings
against that woman.

684
00:45:11.871 --> 00:45:18.960
I felt I had to speak up for the
sake of public health and safety.

685
00:45:19.337 --> 00:45:22.864
But this could be seen
as snitching or...

686
00:45:22.965 --> 00:45:24.366
Don't you worry.

687
00:45:24.467 --> 00:45:27.035
I won't mention the TB.

688
00:45:27.136 --> 00:45:29.579
I'll just make up some excuse
to dismiss her.

689
00:45:29.680 --> 00:45:31.189
Simply and quietly.

690
00:45:32.808 --> 00:45:35.502
It's the proven way.
That's the best.

691
00:45:35.603 --> 00:45:37.528
Okay then.

692
00:45:48.574 --> 00:45:51.751
Have you... washed your hands?

693
00:46:37.248 --> 00:46:41.318
Mr. Kim. do you know
a good braised ribs place?

694
00:46:41.419 --> 00:46:43.069
Somewhere close by.

695
00:46:43.170 --> 00:46:44.529
Sure.

696
00:46:44.630 --> 00:46:48.391
- Then you'll be eating out?
- That's right.

697
00:46:49.009 --> 00:46:51.936
Why such a craving for
braised ribs today?

698
00:46:52.471 --> 00:46:55.356
Our old housekeeper made
delicious ribs.

699
00:46:56.392 --> 00:46:58.460
The one who quit this week?

700
00:46:58.561 --> 00:47:03.531
My wife wouldn't even
tell me why she quit.

701
00:47:06.152 --> 00:47:11.539
Sure. it's easy enough
to hire a new one.

702
00:47:12.575 --> 00:47:17.187
Still. it's a shame.
She was a great housekeeper

703
00:47:17.288 --> 00:47:18.188
I see.

704
00:47:18.289 --> 00:47:20.857
She kept the house
in great shape.

705
00:47:20.958 --> 00:47:23.634
and she knew never to
cross the line.

706
00:47:24.170 --> 00:47:27.054
I can't stand people
who cross the line.

707
00:47:27.590 --> 00:47:30.266
If just one weak point...

708
00:47:30.885 --> 00:47:32.369
Eating too much?

709
00:47:32.470 --> 00:47:35.396
She always ate two servings.

710
00:47:36.056 --> 00:47:39.918
But considering
all the work she did...

711
00:47:40.019 --> 00:47:45.382
Then you better find someone
quickly. A new housekeeper.

712
00:47:45.483 --> 00:47:47.509
We're in trouble now.

713
00:47:47.610 --> 00:47:52.079
In a week. our house
will be a trash can.

714
00:47:53.115 --> 00:47:56.125
My clothes will start to reek...

715
00:47:57.161 --> 00:48:00.063
My wife has no talent
for housework.

716
00:48:00.164 --> 00:48:03.466
She's bad at cleaning.
and her cooking's awful.

717
00:48:04.502 --> 00:48:06.385
Still. you love her. right?

718
00:48:14.053 --> 00:48:17.396
Of course. I love her.

719
00:48:18.432 --> 00:48:20.316
We'll call it love.

720
00:48:21.936 --> 00:48:24.111
Then would this help?

721
00:48:28.150 --> 00:48:30.343
THE CARE? What is this?

722
00:48:30.444 --> 00:48:32.929
I just recently
found out about them.

723
00:48:33.030 --> 00:48:37.875
How to describe it?
It's a members-only service.

724
00:48:38.452 --> 00:48:44.983
The company provides experienced
help to VIP customers such as you.

725
00:48:45.084 --> 00:48:50.988
For example maids. caregivers.
Or drivers like myself.

726
00:48:51.089 --> 00:48:54.307
You can tell from the card
they're very exclusive.

727
00:48:54.842 --> 00:48:56.434
Cool design.

728
00:48:57.512 --> 00:48:59.496
How did you come
across this company?

729
00:48:59.597 --> 00:49:04.126
They contacted me as a
veteran-grade VIP driver.

730
00:49:04.227 --> 00:49:06.444
A kind of a scout offer?

731
00:49:07.981 --> 00:49:13.719
But when their call came I had
already arranged to meet with you.

732
00:49:13.820 --> 00:49:16.997
I see...

733
00:49:18.032 --> 00:49:21.293
You turned down this prestigious
company to work for me.

734
00:49:21.828 --> 00:49:23.253
I'm forever indebted.

735
00:49:24.789 --> 00:49:27.007
Son of a bitch!

736
00:49:29.043 --> 00:49:32.905
Anyway. I can give this card
to my wife. right?

737
00:49:33.006 --> 00:49:34.781
Yes. that's why I brought it up.

738
00:49:34.882 --> 00:49:37.058
No need to mention me.

739
00:49:38.469 --> 00:49:41.646
You can tell her
you found the company yourself.

740
00:49:42.181 --> 00:49:43.540
Sure.

741
00:49:43.641 --> 00:49:46.001
Thanks to you I can
play the good husband.

742
00:49:46.102 --> 00:49:50.881
On the back. there's
a number for consultations.

743
00:49:50.982 --> 00:49:52.132
Tell her to call there...

744
00:49:52.233 --> 00:49:53.783
Eyes on the road!

745
00:49:58.823 --> 00:50:02.042
Hello. this is Senior Advisor
Yeo Myung-son of The Care.

746
00:50:02.201 --> 00:50:05.670
Yes. is this The Care's main office?

747
00:50:06.456 --> 00:50:09.858
If she wanted. she'd be
a fucking great con artist.

748
00:50:09.959 --> 00:50:12.594
Isn't her tone of voice great?
Takes after me.

749
00:50:14.130 --> 00:50:16.657
From what I've heard.
it's a members-only service?

750
00:50:16.758 --> 00:50:20.619
So you're not currently
a member. I assume?

751
00:50:20.720 --> 00:50:23.247
That's right.
What steps do I need to take?

752
00:50:23.348 --> 00:50:27.459
We'll just need a few documents.

753
00:50:27.560 --> 00:50:30.546
Are you ready to write this down?

754
00:50:30.647 --> 00:50:35.533
Your family register.
ID cards...

755
00:50:36.235 --> 00:50:39.179
documents to verify
your income level.

756
00:50:39.280 --> 00:50:41.723
the title to your property. etc.

757
00:50:41.824 --> 00:50:44.250
Our property title? Yes.

758
00:50:52.794 --> 00:50:54.111
Wow. peaches!

759
00:50:54.212 --> 00:50:56.346
You have some too. Mr. Kevin.

760
00:50:56.464 --> 00:50:57.806
Thank you.

761
00:51:06.307 --> 00:51:09.334
Leave it outside the door
next time.

762
00:51:09.435 --> 00:51:11.569
- And knock!
- Yes.

763
00:51:14.148 --> 00:51:15.757
Never enter during sessions!

764
00:51:15.858 --> 00:51:17.283
Yes. miss!

765
00:51:19.362 --> 00:51:20.762
Park Da-song!

766
00:51:20.863 --> 00:51:22.097
Daddy!

767
00:51:22.198 --> 00:51:23.665
Where are you?

768
00:51:28.204 --> 00:51:29.229
Daddy!

769
00:51:29.330 --> 00:51:30.188
Son!

770
00:51:30.289 --> 00:51:33.191
Walkie talkies!

771
00:51:33.292 --> 00:51:34.361
Walkie talkies!

772
00:51:34.385 --> 00:51:37.429
What do you like better.
me or the walkie talkies?

773
00:51:37.764 --> 00:51:41.033
Da-song. how could you
run out from your lesson?

774
00:51:41.134 --> 00:51:44.703
When did you buy all this?

775
00:51:44.804 --> 00:51:45.823
It's no big deal.

776
00:51:45.847 --> 00:51:46.947
Huh?

777
00:51:49.800 --> 00:51:51.031
Huh?

778
00:51:51.542 --> 00:51:53.248
What is it?

779
00:51:55.773 --> 00:51:57.240
What's he doing now?

780
00:51:58.076 --> 00:51:59.468
Da-song. that's enough!

781
00:51:59.569 --> 00:52:03.388
It's the same!
They smell the same!

782
00:52:03.489 --> 00:52:07.100
What are you talking about?
Go up to Jessica.

783
00:52:07.201 --> 00:52:11.254
Jessica smells like that. too.

784
00:52:12.290 --> 00:52:15.609
So do we all need to use
different soaps now?

785
00:52:15.710 --> 00:52:19.571
Dad. we'll need to use different
laundry detergents too.

786
00:52:19.672 --> 00:52:20.781
And fabric softeners.

787
00:52:20.882 --> 00:52:25.202
You mean. we run the laundry for
each person separately? Geez.

788
00:52:25.303 --> 00:52:27.228
That's not it.

789
00:52:27.847 --> 00:52:30.065
It's the semi-basement stench.

790
00:52:31.100 --> 00:52:33.902
To lose the smell.
we have to leave this place.

791
00:52:35.563 --> 00:52:41.551
Anyway. aren't we fortunate to be
worrying about things like this?

792
00:52:41.652 --> 00:52:42.678
Sure.

793
00:52:42.779 --> 00:52:45.889
These days. even an opening
for a security guard

794
00:52:45.990 --> 00:52:50.686
attracts 500 university graduates.

795
00:52:50.787 --> 00:52:54.047
And our entire family got hired!

796
00:52:54.582 --> 00:52:56.216
That's right. Dad!

797
00:52:56.751 --> 00:52:59.194
Put all our salaries together...

798
00:52:59.295 --> 00:53:03.640
the amount of cash coming from
their house into ours is no joke!

799
00:53:04.217 --> 00:53:08.745
Let's offer a prayer of gratitude
to the great Mr. Park.

800
00:53:08.846 --> 00:53:09.955
And to Min-hyuk!

801
00:53:10.056 --> 00:53:12.708
Ki-woo is an amazing friend!

802
00:53:12.809 --> 00:53:17.112
Thanks to him we're all...
Fuck. not again!

803
00:53:21.676 --> 00:53:22.676
That asshole's dead.

804
00:53:22.777 --> 00:53:25.303
Ki-woo's got the spunk!

805
00:53:25.404 --> 00:53:28.081
Don't overdo it!

806
00:53:29.116 --> 00:53:31.668
Use this instead.

807
00:53:35.206 --> 00:53:36.840
Damn you!

808
00:53:39.377 --> 00:53:40.610
Get a fucking grip!

809
00:53:40.711 --> 00:53:42.637
Get a grip!

810
00:53:44.674 --> 00:53:46.432
Wow!

811
00:53:50.471 --> 00:53:52.897
Total inundation!

812
00:54:09.365 --> 00:54:13.143
Current weather is clear. over.
The clouds are moving.

813
00:54:13.244 --> 00:54:15.645
But they're not rain clouds. over.

814
00:54:15.746 --> 00:54:17.105
Copy. over.

815
00:54:17.206 --> 00:54:23.528
Currently your sister's lips
are pouting like a duck's bill.

816
00:54:23.629 --> 00:54:26.615
She's super annoyed. over.

817
00:54:26.716 --> 00:54:31.453
Can't I stay home and study English?
And call Kevin?

818
00:54:31.554 --> 00:54:34.915
Hey! Don't make a fuss
just as we're leaving.

819
00:54:35.016 --> 00:54:37.334
If we have to go.
let's have some fun.

820
00:54:37.435 --> 00:54:40.086
Da-hye. this is no
ordinary camping trip.

821
00:54:40.187 --> 00:54:41.021
That's right!

822
00:54:41.022 --> 00:54:42.847
How could you miss
your brother's birthday?

823
00:54:42.948 --> 00:54:43.840
No way!

824
00:54:43.941 --> 00:54:46.218
Even your busy father
is taking time off to go.

825
00:54:46.319 --> 00:54:49.245
Right! If you don't go.
you'll regret it!

826
00:54:51.574 --> 00:54:53.725
Oh. right.
You know the beam projector?

827
00:54:53.826 --> 00:54:54.845
That outdoor projecting thing?

828
00:54:54.869 --> 00:54:57.045
Right. bring the outdoor
beam projector.

829
00:54:57.538 --> 00:55:02.025
And look for Da-song's
camping raincoat.

830
00:55:02.126 --> 00:55:04.052
He loves it when it rains.

831
00:55:04.587 --> 00:55:08.281
You remember now?
Zoonie. Berry. and Fofoo.

832
00:55:08.382 --> 00:55:09.449
Zoonie and Berry get this.

833
00:55:09.550 --> 00:55:12.369
Yes. Natural Balance Original Ultra.

834
00:55:12.470 --> 00:55:14.938
Right. and for Foofoo...

835
00:55:15.473 --> 00:55:16.742
Kam-kamaboko.
The Japanese crab sticks.

836
00:55:16.766 --> 00:55:17.791
Yes.

837
00:55:17.892 --> 00:55:20.835
When you walk Zoonie.
give him a long leash.

838
00:55:20.936 --> 00:55:23.296
He needs to run around a lot
to be happy.

839
00:55:23.397 --> 00:55:26.824
He's like the canine version
of Da-song!

840
00:55:52.385 --> 00:55:54.160
Son!

841
00:55:54.261 --> 00:55:57.289
What are you doing lying out there?

842
00:55:57.390 --> 00:56:00.274
Isn't he hot out there?

843
00:56:00.810 --> 00:56:05.529
I'm gazing at the sky from home.

844
00:56:07.065 --> 00:56:08.657
It's so great.

845
00:56:12.195 --> 00:56:14.179
Mom. want some water?

846
00:56:14.280 --> 00:56:15.723
There's sparkling. right?

847
00:56:15.824 --> 00:56:18.309
Ki-Jung. some water?

848
00:56:18.410 --> 00:56:20.544
Telepathy... thank you.

849
00:56:42.684 --> 00:56:44.276
Whoa.

850
00:56:46.438 --> 00:56:49.448
Wow. all these different
kinds of liquor.

851
00:56:50.567 --> 00:56:53.927
Dad! Let me add
another to the mix!

852
00:56:54.028 --> 00:56:58.540
This is pretty classy.

853
00:56:59.075 --> 00:57:04.229
Rain falling on the lawn.
as we sip our whiskey...

854
00:57:04.330 --> 00:57:09.051
Ki-woo. what's that yellow
notebook you've been carrying?

855
00:57:09.711 --> 00:57:13.155
This? It's Da-hye's diary.

856
00:57:13.256 --> 00:57:14.740
Her diary?

857
00:57:14.841 --> 00:57:19.102
That's disgusting.
Why are you reading her diary?

858
00:57:19.637 --> 00:57:24.917
So we can understand
each other more deeply.

859
00:57:25.018 --> 00:57:27.736
Fuck. are you two dating?

860
00:57:27.896 --> 00:57:32.365
I'm serious.
She likes me a lot. too.

861
00:57:34.152 --> 00:57:35.744
A while back...

862
00:57:36.780 --> 00:57:38.038
Never mind.

863
00:57:39.073 --> 00:57:41.975
When she enters university.
I'll officially ask her out.

864
00:57:42.076 --> 00:57:43.460
Seriously.

865
00:57:48.041 --> 00:57:50.092
My son!

866
00:57:50.251 --> 00:57:54.846
Then this house will be
your in-laws' house?

867
00:57:57.242 --> 00:57:58.242
That's right.

868
00:57:58.343 --> 00:58:02.162
Fuck. then I'm washing
in-law's dishes?

869
00:58:02.263 --> 00:58:05.941
Sure. washing your
daughter-in-law's socks!

870
00:58:17.487 --> 00:58:22.933
I like her. She's a good kid.

871
00:58:23.034 --> 00:58:27.337
Pretty-like. but
not spoiled rotten.

872
00:58:28.373 --> 00:58:32.551
Well. now that
we're daydreaming...

873
00:58:33.628 --> 00:58:36.238
If Da-hye and I get married...

874
00:58:36.339 --> 00:58:40.183
we can bring in actors
to be my mom and dad.

875
00:58:41.161 --> 00:58:42.161
Look at her.

876
00:58:42.262 --> 00:58:46.123
She did so many part-time gigs
at weddings last year.

877
00:58:46.224 --> 00:58:50.544
Even caught the bouquet
from bitches I've never met.

878
00:58:50.645 --> 00:58:53.630
If you get the bouquet.
they pay an extra $10.

879
00:58:53.731 --> 00:58:55.758
That's how your acting
improved so much!

880
00:58:55.859 --> 00:59:01.346
Acting is one thing. but this
family is so gullible. right?

881
00:59:01.447 --> 00:59:03.640
The madame especially.

882
00:59:03.741 --> 00:59:05.750
You said it.

883
00:59:07.287 --> 00:59:10.856
She's so naive. and so nice.

884
00:59:10.957 --> 00:59:12.858
She's rich. but still nice.

885
00:59:12.959 --> 00:59:15.319
It's not "rich. but still nice."

886
00:59:15.420 --> 00:59:19.347
It's "Nice because she's rich."
You know?

887
00:59:19.883 --> 00:59:26.396
Hell. if I had all this money.

888
00:59:27.432 --> 00:59:31.335
I'd be nice too!

889
00:59:31.436 --> 00:59:32.944
Even nicer!

890
00:59:33.104 --> 00:59:35.422
That's true. Your mom's right.

891
00:59:35.523 --> 00:59:37.925
Rich people are naive.
Not tied up in knots all the time.

892
00:59:38.026 --> 00:59:40.302
No wrinkles on them.

893
00:59:40.403 --> 00:59:43.806
It all gets ironed out.
Money is the iron.

894
00:59:43.907 --> 00:59:46.308
Those wrinkles all get smoothed out.

895
00:59:46.409 --> 00:59:47.959
Hey. Ki-woo.

896
00:59:48.578 --> 00:59:53.632
You know that driver. Yoon?
Was it Yoon?

897
00:59:54.167 --> 00:59:56.401
The driver before me.

898
00:59:56.502 --> 00:59:57.694
Yeah. Yoon.

899
00:59:57.795 --> 01:00:02.366
He must be working
somewhere else now. right?

900
01:00:02.467 --> 01:00:04.785
Sure. he must be.

901
01:00:04.886 --> 01:00:08.480
He's young. got a good physique.

902
01:00:09.015 --> 01:00:12.084
He must've found a better job.

903
01:00:12.185 --> 01:00:14.277
Fucking hell!

904
01:00:14.812 --> 01:00:17.297
What's with her now?

905
01:00:17.398 --> 01:00:23.870
We're the ones who need help.
Worry about us. okay?

906
01:00:23.988 --> 01:00:27.391
Dad! Come on. Dad!

907
01:00:27.492 --> 01:00:31.812
Just focus on us. okay? On us!

908
01:00:31.913 --> 01:00:36.233
Not Driver Yoon. but me. please.

909
01:00:36.334 --> 01:00:38.569
Killer timing. huh?

910
01:00:38.670 --> 01:00:42.764
She speaks.
and the lightning crashes!

911
01:00:44.425 --> 01:00:47.519
Hey. Jessica. Cheers.

912
01:00:48.554 --> 01:00:54.001
Hey. when I went up before.
and you were in the bath...

913
01:00:54.102 --> 01:00:56.027
What about it?

914
01:00:56.562 --> 01:00:59.965
How to put it? You fit right in.

915
01:01:00.066 --> 01:01:02.701
This rich house suits you
very well. Not like us.

916
01:01:02.802 --> 01:01:03.802
Fuck off.

917
01:01:03.903 --> 01:01:04.761
I'm serious!

918
01:01:04.862 --> 01:01:06.513
Dad. earlier...

919
01:01:06.614 --> 01:01:09.499
She was lying back in the tub.
watching TV.

920
01:01:10.034 --> 01:01:12.585
Like she's lived here for years.

921
01:01:14.163 --> 01:01:20.110
Speaking of which.
if this became our house.

922
01:01:20.211 --> 01:01:24.448
if we lived here.
which room would you want?

923
01:01:24.549 --> 01:01:29.745
What room in this masterpiece
of the great Nam-goong?

924
01:01:29.846 --> 01:01:31.705
Fuck. I don't know.

925
01:01:31.806 --> 01:01:35.608
Get me the house first.
Then I'll worry about it.

926
01:01:36.144 --> 01:01:38.278
We live here now. don't we?

927
01:01:38.813 --> 01:01:42.615
Getting drunk in the living room.

928
01:01:42.734 --> 01:01:45.469
Right. we live here. Why not?

929
01:01:45.570 --> 01:01:50.223
This is our home right now.
It's cosy.

930
01:01:50.324 --> 01:01:53.310
Cosy? Are you feeling cosy?

931
01:01:53.411 --> 01:01:58.506
Sure. but suppose Mr. Park
walked through that door now.

932
01:01:59.042 --> 01:02:00.359
What about your dad?

933
01:02:00.460 --> 01:02:04.095
He'd run and hide
like a cockroach.

934
01:02:04.630 --> 01:02:06.782
Kids. you know at our house.

935
01:02:06.883 --> 01:02:12.621
when you turn on the light.
and the cockroaches scatter?

936
01:02:12.722 --> 01:02:14.606
You know what I mean?

937
01:02:15.183 --> 01:02:18.526
I'm getting fucking tired of this.

938
01:02:19.062 --> 01:02:20.945
- A cockroach?
- Yeah.

939
01:02:24.484 --> 01:02:26.343
Huh? What's wrong?

940
01:02:26.444 --> 01:02:27.552
What's the matter?

941
01:02:27.653 --> 01:02:31.664
Dad. don't do that.
You're gonna kill somebody.

942
01:02:38.706 --> 01:02:40.399
What the hell?

943
01:02:40.500 --> 01:02:42.109
I fooled you! Didn't I?

944
01:02:42.210 --> 01:02:43.527
Jesus. Dad.

945
01:02:43.628 --> 01:02:47.698
I fooled you too. Ki-woo?
Very real. wasn't it?

946
01:02:47.799 --> 01:02:51.493
If it was for real.
you'd be dead. you fucker!

947
01:02:51.594 --> 01:02:55.647
What is this? Fucking puppy.

948
01:03:01.187 --> 01:03:03.422
Who is it at this hour'?

949
01:03:03.523 --> 01:03:05.407
Who is it?

950
01:03:11.572 --> 01:03:12.681
What's she doing here?

951
01:03:12.782 --> 01:03:15.875
The old housekeeper?

952
01:03:16.410 --> 01:03:18.253
What's she here for?

953
01:03:18.788 --> 01:03:22.673
She won't stop ringing it.

954
01:03:23.708 --> 01:03:26.593
Raising a racket.

955
01:03:27.571 --> 01:03:28.571
Who is it?

956
01:03:28.672 --> 01:03:33.492
Oh. hello! I'm...

957
01:03:33.593 --> 01:03:35.202
The madame's not in. right?

958
01:03:35.303 --> 01:03:36.203
What?

959
01:03:36.304 --> 01:03:40.899
I worked here
for a very long time.

960
01:03:41.434 --> 01:03:46.964
Above the monitor there.
you see a photo of 3 dogs. right?

961
01:03:47.065 --> 01:03:48.507
Zoonie. Berry. Foofoo.

962
01:03:48.608 --> 01:03:53.137
I get it. but why are you here?

963
01:03:53.238 --> 01:03:57.875
You're my successor
as housekeeper. right?

964
01:04:02.914 --> 01:04:04.673
Anyway...

965
01:04:05.208 --> 01:04:08.486
I'm very sorry to
call on you so late.

966
01:04:08.587 --> 01:04:10.471
It's just that...

967
01:04:11.006 --> 01:04:17.769
I forgot something in the
basement under the kitchen.

968
01:04:18.305 --> 01:04:24.693
When I quit.
they pushed me out so quickly...

969
01:04:27.772 --> 01:04:29.948
Would you let me in?

970
01:04:31.985 --> 01:04:34.077
What do we do?

971
01:04:34.613 --> 01:04:36.872
This wasn't in the plan.

972
01:04:44.414 --> 01:04:46.131
Sorry for the trouble.

973
01:04:46.691 --> 01:04:47.691
This way.

974
01:04:47.792 --> 01:04:49.426
Yes. thank you.

975
01:04:51.463 --> 01:04:53.405
You can put your raincoat...

976
01:04:53.506 --> 01:04:56.099
It'll just be a second.

977
01:04:56.676 --> 01:05:00.329
You did a lot of cooking there.
That'll be a job to clean up.

978
01:05:00.430 --> 01:05:03.815
But what did you leave below?

979
01:05:08.355 --> 01:05:10.948
Want to come down with me?

980
01:05:11.983 --> 01:05:15.327
Just be back quickly.

981
01:06:08.415 --> 01:06:11.758
Help me push this!

982
01:06:11.876 --> 01:06:14.361
Pull it! From over there.

983
01:06:14.462 --> 01:06:16.030
What?

984
01:06:16.131 --> 01:06:17.231
Pull!

985
01:06:20.051 --> 01:06:21.602
Harder!

986
01:06:25.140 --> 01:06:26.648
Are you alright?

987
01:06:28.184 --> 01:06:29.484
I startled you.

988
01:06:32.022 --> 01:06:33.572
Thank you!

989
01:06:34.649 --> 01:06:36.074
Thank you.

990
01:06:44.059 --> 01:06:45.059
Honey!

991
01:06:45.160 --> 01:06:46.293
What the hell?

992
01:06:47.829 --> 01:06:48.896
Hey!

993
01:06:48.997 --> 01:06:50.547
Honey!

994
01:06:51.583 --> 01:06:53.133
Honey!

995
01:06:55.528 --> 01:06:56.528
Wait!

996
01:06:56.629 --> 01:06:58.822
Honey. I'm here!

997
01:06:58.923 --> 01:07:00.223
What is all this?

998
01:07:02.761 --> 01:07:03.861
Honey!

999
01:07:04.137 --> 01:07:05.788
Honey. I'm fine.

1000
01:07:05.889 --> 01:07:07.648
No you're not!

1001
01:07:07.749 --> 01:07:08.749
I'm fine. really.

1002
01:07:08.850 --> 01:07:10.084
You are not fine!

1003
01:07:10.185 --> 01:07:11.961
I'm so hungry.

1004
01:07:12.062 --> 01:07:12.962
Take this. Take this.

1005
01:07:13.063 --> 01:07:16.298
How many days has it been?

1006
01:07:16.399 --> 01:07:18.116
You must've been so hungry!

1007
01:07:20.153 --> 01:07:21.428
It's okay.

1008
01:07:21.529 --> 01:07:24.223
She's a good woman.
I got in. thanks to her.

1009
01:07:24.324 --> 01:07:26.433
There was an iron plate.
for grilling meat.

1010
01:07:26.534 --> 01:07:27.977
It was wedged under the shelf.

1011
01:07:28.078 --> 01:07:29.144
No wonder.

1012
01:07:29.245 --> 01:07:32.648
I couldn't open it from the inside.

1013
01:07:32.749 --> 01:07:36.259
- What's going on here?
- I know you must be startled.

1014
01:07:36.378 --> 01:07:38.970
I would be too in this situation.

1015
01:07:39.089 --> 01:07:43.617
But as two fellow workers...
Right. Chung-sook?

1016
01:07:43.718 --> 01:07:46.561
How do you know my name?

1017
01:07:47.097 --> 01:07:51.792
To be honest I'm still texting
with the boy Da-song.

1018
01:07:51.893 --> 01:07:56.463
I knew they were going camping.
so I came today.

1019
01:07:56.564 --> 01:07:59.341
I wanted to speak with you privately.

1020
01:07:59.442 --> 01:08:00.617
Talking about.

1021
01:08:03.154 --> 01:08:05.472
Don't worry. Chung-sook.

1022
01:08:05.573 --> 01:08:09.310
I cut the wire
to the CCTV by the gate.

1023
01:08:09.411 --> 01:08:13.022
Nobody knows I came.
Isn't that good. sister?

1024
01:08:13.123 --> 01:08:15.190
Sister? Do you know me?

1025
01:08:15.291 --> 01:08:18.260
Sister. my name is Moon-gwang.

1026
01:08:18.795 --> 01:08:22.865
This is my hubby Oh Geun-sae.
Say hello. honey.

1027
01:08:22.966 --> 01:08:26.285
This tastes great.
What happened to your face?

1028
01:08:26.386 --> 01:08:29.229
I'll tell you some other time.

1029
01:08:29.806 --> 01:08:33.709
So. while working here.
you looted the kitchen everyday.

1030
01:08:33.810 --> 01:08:34.835
To feed your husband.

1031
01:08:34.936 --> 01:08:39.590
Not at all! I bought
all his food with my salary.

1032
01:08:39.691 --> 01:08:42.760
That's so unfair!

1033
01:08:42.861 --> 01:08:45.471
But how long has
your husband been down here?

1034
01:08:45.572 --> 01:08:48.415
Oh my. hold on... 4 years?

1035
01:08:48.950 --> 01:08:51.602
4 years. 3 months and 17 days.

1036
01:08:51.703 --> 01:08:53.670
Right. it's June now.

1037
01:08:54.205 --> 01:09:00.093
Four years ago when
Mr. Nam-goong moved to Paris.

1038
01:09:00.253 --> 01:09:03.263
in the time before
Mr. Park's family moved in.

1039
01:09:03.423 --> 01:09:06.867
I brought my husband down here.

1040
01:09:06.968 --> 01:09:11.997
Many rich houses have secret bunkers.
where you can hide

1041
01:09:12.098 --> 01:09:16.627
in case North Korea attacks.
or if creditors break in.

1042
01:09:16.728 --> 01:09:22.908
But it seems Mr. Nam-goong was
a bit embarrassed about this.

1043
01:09:23.067 --> 01:09:26.929
because he never mentioned it
to Mr. Park's family.

1044
01:09:27.030 --> 01:09:28.347
So only I knew about it.

1045
01:09:28.448 --> 01:09:30.933
So that's how it all happened.

1046
01:09:31.034 --> 01:09:35.145
But now that I know. I've no
choice but to call the police!

1047
01:09:35.246 --> 01:09:37.672
No please. sister!

1048
01:09:38.291 --> 01:09:40.567
We're both needy people.
please don't.

1049
01:09:40.668 --> 01:09:42.069
I'm not needy!

1050
01:09:42.170 --> 01:09:45.948
But we are needy!

1051
01:09:46.049 --> 01:09:50.536
We've no house. no money.
only debts!

1052
01:09:50.637 --> 01:09:51.787
Sister. please!

1053
01:09:51.888 --> 01:09:56.333
Even with 4 years of hiding.
debt collectors never let up.

1054
01:09:56.434 --> 01:10:00.587
They're still searching for him.
threatening to mangle him.

1055
01:10:00.688 --> 01:10:02.489
You borrowed from loan sharks?

1056
01:10:03.149 --> 01:10:05.367
It's all my fault.

1057
01:10:05.902 --> 01:10:07.202
The Taiwan cake shop.

1058
01:10:07.737 --> 01:10:11.515
My Taiwanese Wangshui
castella shop went bust.

1059
01:10:11.616 --> 01:10:13.892
I fell into big debt.

1060
01:10:13.993 --> 01:10:15.752
Please take this.

1061
01:10:15.870 --> 01:10:17.254
What's that?

1062
01:10:17.789 --> 01:10:21.650
It's not much.
just a modest sum.

1063
01:10:21.751 --> 01:10:24.737
But we'll send it
to you every month.

1064
01:10:24.838 --> 01:10:26.572
In return.
just once every two days

1065
01:10:26.673 --> 01:10:30.142
please leave him some food.

1066
01:10:30.677 --> 01:10:33.687
No no. just once a week.

1067
01:10:34.222 --> 01:10:36.414
There's a refrigerator here.
Just once a week.

1068
01:10:36.515 --> 01:10:38.958
You've got some nerve!
I'm calling the police.

1069
01:10:39.059 --> 01:10:40.276
Sister. sister!

1070
01:10:43.313 --> 01:10:44.530
What's that?

1071
01:10:47.568 --> 01:10:49.451
Wait... Jessica?

1072
01:10:49.987 --> 01:10:51.012
Mr. Kim?

1073
01:10:51.113 --> 01:10:52.213
What the hell?

1074
01:10:53.699 --> 01:10:54.766
Dad. my ankle!

1075
01:10:54.867 --> 01:10:56.058
Don't press it!

1076
01:10:56.159 --> 01:10:58.060
Father. my arm!

1077
01:10:58.161 --> 01:10:59.837
Don't call me Dad!

1078
01:11:07.379 --> 01:11:11.182
I thought it was weird
when the driver was fired.

1079
01:11:11.408 --> 01:11:12.408
Hey.

1080
01:11:12.509 --> 01:11:14.952
- Let's talk things over.
- What the hell?

1081
01:11:15.053 --> 01:11:16.412
Are you some
family of charlatans?

1082
01:11:16.513 --> 01:11:17.330
So. sister...

1083
01:11:17.431 --> 01:11:19.940
Don't fucking call me sister.
you filthy bitch!

1084
01:11:20.475 --> 01:11:25.254
I'm gonna send this video to
Mrs. Park. how about that?

1085
01:11:25.355 --> 01:11:27.548
Dad. my arm!

1086
01:11:27.649 --> 01:11:29.867
No reception in
the basement. right?

1087
01:11:30.402 --> 01:11:32.261
- The phone works fine.
- Fuck.

1088
01:11:32.362 --> 01:11:36.974
Ma'am. to be honest.
the jobs we have here...

1089
01:11:37.075 --> 01:11:40.102
Shut up! It's too late now!

1090
01:11:40.203 --> 01:11:43.439
Let's all go to jail!
We're fucking going down!

1091
01:11:43.540 --> 01:11:47.051
Lady. are you crazy?

1092
01:11:47.586 --> 01:11:52.573
If they see that video. Mr. Park
and his wife will be so shocked!

1093
01:11:52.674 --> 01:11:56.060
What did those nice people
ever do wrong?

1094
01:11:56.411 --> 01:11:57.411
Why do this to them?

1095
01:11:57.512 --> 01:11:59.205
Stop right there!

1096
01:11:59.306 --> 01:12:01.666
Or I'll push the 'send' button.

1097
01:12:01.767 --> 01:12:03.734
Follow me.

1098
01:12:04.269 --> 01:12:06.695
Calm down. ma'am.

1099
01:12:10.233 --> 01:12:12.284
Don't push!

1100
01:12:13.320 --> 01:12:14.828
Let's go up. honey.

1101
01:12:15.364 --> 01:12:18.249
Time for you to get
some fresh air!

1102
01:12:35.300 --> 01:12:41.605
Honey. this 'send' button
is like a missile launcher.

1103
01:12:41.765 --> 01:12:43.524
What do you mean. honey?

1104
01:12:44.101 --> 01:12:49.380
If we threaten to push it.
Those people can't do anything.

1105
01:12:49.481 --> 01:12:53.993
It's like a North Korean rocket.
A North Korean missile button!

1106
01:12:55.529 --> 01:12:58.973
Today our beloved
Great Leader Kim Jong-un.

1107
01:12:59.074 --> 01:13:02.143
after witnessing the
charlatan family video.

1108
01:13:02.244 --> 01:13:04.979
was unable to contain
his shock and fury

1109
01:13:05.080 --> 01:13:08.316
at their wicked.
despicable provocations!

1110
01:13:08.417 --> 01:13:10.192
I've missed your jokes. honey!

1111
01:13:10.293 --> 01:13:14.822
Therefore our Great Leader.
in this age of de-nuclearization.

1112
01:13:14.923 --> 01:13:20.703
has commanded that the nation's
last remaining nuclear warhead

1113
01:13:20.804 --> 01:13:23.289
be driven down the throats
of this wicked family!

1114
01:13:23.390 --> 01:13:28.085
No one can imitate North Korean
news anchors like you!

1115
01:13:28.186 --> 01:13:33.215
With their stinking guts serving
as the last nuclear graveyard.

1116
01:13:33.316 --> 01:13:38.220
our Dear Leaders wish to de-nuclearize
and bring world peace...

1117
01:13:38.321 --> 01:13:40.331
Hands in the air. fuckers!

1118
01:13:40.866 --> 01:13:41.999
Higher!

1119
01:13:43.910 --> 01:13:45.937
You scumbag family.

1120
01:13:46.038 --> 01:13:47.112
Husband?

1121
01:13:47.213 --> 01:13:48.022
Husband.

1122
01:13:48.123 --> 01:13:48.906
Wife?

1123
01:13:49.007 --> 01:13:49.857
Yes.

1124
01:13:49.958 --> 01:13:50.958
Son?

1125
01:13:51.059 --> 01:13:51.925
Yes.

1126
01:13:51.926 --> 01:13:52.985
- Daughter?
- Daughter.

1127
01:13:53.086 --> 01:13:55.029
You low-lifes!

1128
01:13:55.130 --> 01:13:59.492
Is that all you can think to do.
drink yourselves stupid?

1129
01:13:59.593 --> 01:14:04.872
In Mr. Nam-goon's living room
where his creative soul dwells?

1130
01:14:04.973 --> 01:14:05.998
You cretins!

1131
01:14:06.099 --> 01:14:07.416
What do you know about art?

1132
01:14:07.517 --> 01:14:09.777
What would they know?

1133
01:14:10.437 --> 01:14:18.360
On a sunny day. the two of us
would bask in the sunbeam.

1134
01:14:19.196 --> 01:14:23.832
In those moments we could feel
his artistic touch.

1135
01:15:11.706 --> 01:15:15.217
Give it to me!

1136
01:15:34.271 --> 01:15:37.781
Good job! Delete it!

1137
01:15:38.817 --> 01:15:41.410
Careful. don't send it
by accident.

1138
01:15:55.959 --> 01:15:57.059
Hello?

1139
01:15:57.586 --> 01:16:01.096
Listen. do you know how
to make Chapa-guri?

1140
01:16:01.631 --> 01:16:02.865
Chapa-guri?

1141
01:16:02.966 --> 01:16:06.643
Chapa-guri is Da-song's favorite.

1142
01:16:06.803 --> 01:16:10.498
If you boil the water now.
the timing will be perfect.

1143
01:16:10.599 --> 01:16:13.334
There's premium sirloin in the
fridge. Add that too.

1144
01:16:13.435 --> 01:16:14.960
Then. the camping...?

1145
01:16:15.061 --> 01:16:18.780
My god. what a disaster.

1146
01:16:19.316 --> 01:16:24.578
A nearby river overflowed and
everyone was packing their tents.

1147
01:16:24.696 --> 01:16:27.723
but Da-song was crying and
refusing to go home.

1148
01:16:27.824 --> 01:16:31.960
Anyway. Chapa-guri
as soon as we walk in. okay?

1149
01:16:32.078 --> 01:16:34.563
Then you're almost here?

1150
01:16:34.664 --> 01:16:37.216
8 minutes. according to the GPS.

1151
01:16:37.609 --> 01:16:38.686
You arrive in 8 minutes...

1152
01:16:38.710 --> 01:16:42.429
Start boiling
the water right away!

1153
01:16:46.468 --> 01:16:48.185
What the hell is Chapa-guri?

1154
01:16:57.229 --> 01:16:59.029
Get up. quickly!

1155
01:17:00.815 --> 01:17:01.915
Move!

1156
01:17:08.782 --> 01:17:10.749
Ramen/Udon.

1157
01:17:12.285 --> 01:17:15.337
Dad. I can't drag her
any further!

1158
01:17:26.383 --> 01:17:28.267
What are you doing?

1159
01:17:29.386 --> 01:17:31.228
Dad!

1160
01:17:34.266 --> 01:17:37.484
Go up quickly! Help upstairs.

1161
01:17:45.026 --> 01:17:46.126
Take this!

1162
01:18:05.462 --> 01:18:06.654
Welcome home!

1163
01:18:06.755 --> 01:18:10.099
Da-song. look!
Let's eat Chapa-guri!

1164
01:18:12.261 --> 01:18:13.769
Da-song!

1165
01:18:16.390 --> 01:18:18.399
Da-song!

1166
01:18:24.940 --> 01:18:26.324
Madame!

1167
01:18:44.918 --> 01:18:46.778
Why don't you just
eat the Chapa-guri?

1168
01:18:46.879 --> 01:18:47.654
Shall I?

1169
01:18:47.755 --> 01:18:50.823
No. wait.
I can give it to my husband.

1170
01:18:50.924 --> 01:18:53.017
There's premium sirloin in here.

1171
01:18:55.554 --> 01:18:59.315
It's cooked through?
Medium well done.

1172
01:19:24.375 --> 01:19:30.280
Returning after a day's work...
I love you so much. Mr. Park!

1173
01:19:30.381 --> 01:19:36.894
Home from the office.
Mr. Park is off duty now.

1174
01:19:38.555 --> 01:19:42.834
Returning after a day's work...
I love you so much. Mr. Park!

1175
01:19:42.935 --> 01:19:45.027
- What are you doing?
- Shut up!

1176
01:19:56.573 --> 01:19:58.975
Honey. do you want
some Chapa-guri?

1177
01:19:59.076 --> 01:20:00.101
Da-song doesn't want it?

1178
01:20:00.202 --> 01:20:00.852
No.

1179
01:20:00.953 --> 01:20:02.878
No. I'm tired. I'm going to bed.

1180
01:20:03.414 --> 01:20:06.173
Why are you staring?

1181
01:20:07.209 --> 01:20:10.695
Mr. Park. you feed me
and house me.

1182
01:20:10.796 --> 01:20:12.304
Respect!

1183
01:20:14.341 --> 01:20:16.016
You do this every day?

1184
01:20:16.552 --> 01:20:22.022
Sure. I even send whole
sentences to thank him.

1185
01:20:22.558 --> 01:20:24.667
Someone of your age
should know this.

1186
01:20:24.768 --> 01:20:25.626
Know what?

1187
01:20:25.727 --> 01:20:27.528
Morse Code.

1188
01:20:28.105 --> 01:20:32.116
That sensor's going batty.

1189
01:20:40.284 --> 01:20:43.811
Da-song will know it.
since he's a Scout.

1190
01:20:43.912 --> 01:20:45.605
It looks ridiculous. doesn't it?

1191
01:20:45.706 --> 01:20:49.192
Why make so much fuss
trying to please a kid.

1192
01:20:49.293 --> 01:20:51.277
He's not some kind of prince.

1193
01:20:51.378 --> 01:20:54.138
He's the youngest.
It's understandable.

1194
01:20:55.174 --> 01:20:56.682
Please understand.

1195
01:20:57.217 --> 01:21:00.978
Da-song's a bit... unwell.

1196
01:21:01.221 --> 01:21:04.273
He's receiving trauma therapy
and art therapy.

1197
01:21:05.184 --> 01:21:07.210
There was an incident.

1198
01:21:07.311 --> 01:21:08.694
What incident?

1199
01:21:08.979 --> 01:21:12.907
Sister. you believe in ghosts. too?

1200
01:21:14.026 --> 01:21:17.953
Da-song saw a ghost in the house
when he was in first grade.

1201
01:21:24.495 --> 01:21:26.896
He had a birthday party
at home that day.

1202
01:21:26.997 --> 01:21:29.440
Late that night.
when everyone was sleeping.

1203
01:21:29.541 --> 01:21:34.112
Da-song crept down to the kitchen
and took out the leftover cake.

1204
01:21:34.213 --> 01:21:37.281
The whipped cream on
that cake was amazing.

1205
01:21:37.382 --> 01:21:40.309
Even in bed. he couldn't
stop thinking about it.

1206
01:21:40.844 --> 01:21:46.232
So Da-song was sitting.
eating his cake...

1207
01:21:55.776 --> 01:21:58.744
He screamed.
and I ran downstairs.

1208
01:21:59.279 --> 01:22:01.247
and he was all...

1209
01:22:01.782 --> 01:22:07.127
his eyes rolled back in his head.
convulsion. foam in his mouth.

1210
01:22:09.164 --> 01:22:11.399
Have you ever seen a child
go into a seizure?

1211
01:22:11.500 --> 01:22:12.333
No.

1212
01:22:12.334 --> 01:22:17.613
If you can't treat it within
15-minutes. it's all over.

1213
01:22:17.714 --> 01:22:22.893
That's the time you have to reach
the emergency room. 15 minutes.

1214
01:22:24.429 --> 01:22:28.666
How can you live
in a place like this?

1215
01:22:28.767 --> 01:22:31.961
Well. lots of people
live underground.

1216
01:22:32.062 --> 01:22:34.040
There's even more if you
count the semi-basements.

1217
01:22:34.064 --> 01:22:38.659
What are you going to do next?
You don't have a plan?

1218
01:22:38.819 --> 01:22:42.454
I just feel comfortable here.

1219
01:22:43.532 --> 01:22:46.750
It feels like I was born here.

1220
01:22:47.411 --> 01:22:50.688
Maybe I had my
wedding here. too.

1221
01:22:50.789 --> 01:22:54.216
As for the National Pension.
I don't qualify.

1222
01:22:55.335 --> 01:22:58.971
In my old age.
love will comfort me.

1223
01:23:00.507 --> 01:23:05.895
So please.
Let me stay down here.

1224
01:23:07.431 --> 01:23:09.148
Anyway...

1225
01:23:09.683 --> 01:23:14.737
My husband was away on business.
so I had to deal with it all.

1226
01:23:15.355 --> 01:23:19.675
Since then we've always
gone out for his birthday.

1227
01:23:19.776 --> 01:23:22.803
Last year my mother's house.
this year. camping.

1228
01:23:22.904 --> 01:23:27.767
Da-song's dad says
all kids grow up like that.

1229
01:23:27.868 --> 01:23:32.713
They say a ghost in the
house brings wealth.

1230
01:23:33.874 --> 01:23:38.886
Actually. the money's
been good the last few years.

1231
01:24:05.447 --> 01:24:07.498
Oh. man...

1232
01:24:34.059 --> 01:24:36.986
Just stay here for now.

1233
01:24:47.572 --> 01:24:49.623
Zoonie. what's wrong?

1234
01:24:51.660 --> 01:24:53.168
Something under there?

1235
01:24:54.746 --> 01:24:56.505
What is it?

1236
01:24:57.541 --> 01:24:58.757
Damn it!

1237
01:25:00.293 --> 01:25:01.319
- Mom!
- Yeah?

1238
01:25:01.420 --> 01:25:03.821
- How could you?
- What?

1239
01:25:03.922 --> 01:25:08.041
I like Chapa-guri too!
How could you not even ask me?

1240
01:25:08.142 --> 01:25:08.967
Well...

1241
01:25:08.968 --> 01:25:13.038
Da-song didn't want it. so you
asked Dad. then ate it yourself.

1242
01:25:13.139 --> 01:25:15.957
- Want her to make some more?
- That's not the point!

1243
01:25:16.058 --> 01:25:19.753
- Stop fussing over ramen!
- Why didn't you ask me?

1244
01:25:19.854 --> 01:25:23.364
Oh. stop it! Just go to bed.
Go get changed.

1245
01:25:26.939 --> 01:25:28.531
This way!

1246
01:25:29.787 --> 01:25:30.787
Shhh!

1247
01:25:31.026 --> 01:25:34.287
Ki-Jung is under there!
Hurry. hurry!

1248
01:25:37.455 --> 01:25:39.773
One. two. three!
One. two. three!

1249
01:25:39.874 --> 01:25:41.316
Da-song?

1250
01:25:41.417 --> 01:25:44.135
Da-song. cut it out!

1251
01:25:44.670 --> 01:25:47.138
He's gone crazy!
Get an umbrella.

1252
01:25:47.298 --> 01:25:48.806
Hey. Park Da-song!

1253
01:25:50.342 --> 01:25:55.121
That little monster.
What the hell is he doing?

1254
01:25:55.222 --> 01:25:59.000
Da-song. it's time for bed!
Do you know what time it is?

1255
01:25:59.101 --> 01:26:00.201
Here.

1256
01:26:01.145 --> 01:26:02.445
Honey. take this.

1257
01:26:06.025 --> 01:26:12.705
Who do you take after to be
so stubborn! Look at this rain!

1258
01:26:18.245 --> 01:26:21.089
OMG Kevin.
Da-song camping in the yard.

1259
01:26:24.668 --> 01:26:29.097
Channel 3 for emergencies!
Keep it turned on.

1260
01:26:29.673 --> 01:26:32.867
Let me have it.
I can't believe him.

1261
01:26:32.968 --> 01:26:35.603
Just leave him be.
He'll come in when he's tired.

1262
01:26:36.138 --> 01:26:38.798
- I wish you were here.
- But. I am with you.

1263
01:26:38.899 --> 01:26:39.951
Hey. Da-hye!

1264
01:26:39.975 --> 01:26:42.568
Stop using your phone.
Go to bed.

1265
01:26:43.103 --> 01:26:45.547
Go sleep in your room.
We'll take care of things.

1266
01:26:45.648 --> 01:26:48.675
This is the living room.
do you copy?

1267
01:26:48.776 --> 01:26:49.884
Copy. over.

1268
01:26:49.985 --> 01:26:54.180
Daddy is standing by
for emergencies. over.

1269
01:26:54.281 --> 01:26:57.041
Got it. over.

1270
01:26:58.077 --> 01:27:00.019
Is that tent going to leak?

1271
01:27:00.120 --> 01:27:03.440
It's US made. It'll be fine.

1272
01:27:03.541 --> 01:27:06.568
- Should we sleep here?
- What?

1273
01:27:06.669 --> 01:27:08.862
We've got a full view of the tent.

1274
01:27:08.963 --> 01:27:10.822
Good idea.
I'll feel much better.

1275
01:27:10.923 --> 01:27:11.656
Right?

1276
01:27:11.757 --> 01:27:13.766
Let's sleep while
watching over Da-song.

1277
01:27:15.803 --> 01:27:17.228
What a kid...

1278
01:27:26.772 --> 01:27:27.989
Wait a minute.

1279
01:27:30.568 --> 01:27:32.552
Where's that smell coming from?

1280
01:27:32.653 --> 01:27:34.078
What smell?

1281
01:27:34.613 --> 01:27:35.955
Mr. Kim's smell.

1282
01:27:36.490 --> 01:27:37.874
- Mr. Kim?
- Yeah.

1283
01:27:38.492 --> 01:27:39.851
Not sure what you mean.

1284
01:27:39.952 --> 01:27:43.129
Really?
You must have smelled it.

1285
01:27:43.664 --> 01:27:47.233
That smell that wafts through
the car. how to describe it?

1286
01:27:47.334 --> 01:27:49.694
- An old man's smell?
- No no. it's not that.

1287
01:27:49.795 --> 01:27:52.054
What is it?

1288
01:27:52.590 --> 01:27:54.473
Like old dried radish?

1289
01:27:55.092 --> 01:27:56.309
No.

1290
01:27:56.427 --> 01:27:58.661
You know when you boil a rag?

1291
01:27:58.762 --> 01:28:00.146
It smells like that.

1292
01:28:02.683 --> 01:28:09.047
Anyway. even though he always
seems about to cross the line.

1293
01:28:09.148 --> 01:28:12.383
he never actually crosses it.
That's good.

1294
01:28:12.484 --> 01:28:14.118
- I'll give him credit for that.
- Yeah.

1295
01:28:15.237 --> 01:28:17.997
But that stench crosses the line.

1296
01:28:18.532 --> 01:28:20.750
It powers right through
to the back seat.

1297
01:28:20.868 --> 01:28:22.644
What stench?

1298
01:28:22.745 --> 01:28:23.961
I don't know.

1299
01:28:24.997 --> 01:28:27.381
It's hard to describe.

1300
01:28:28.417 --> 01:28:31.861
But you sometimes smell it
on the subways.

1301
01:28:31.962 --> 01:28:35.389
It's been ages
since I rode a subway.

1302
01:28:35.925 --> 01:28:38.868
People who ride the subway
have that special smell.

1303
01:28:38.969 --> 01:28:40.394
Yeah.

1304
01:28:56.528 --> 01:28:59.580
Isn't this like the back
seat of my car?

1305
01:29:00.240 --> 01:29:03.709
What if Da-song comes back in?

1306
01:29:04.244 --> 01:29:05.878
Don't worry!

1307
01:29:06.413 --> 01:29:09.090
I can just pull my hand back.

1308
01:29:14.630 --> 01:29:16.264
We shouldn't...

1309
01:29:22.805 --> 01:29:24.188
Do it clockwise.

1310
01:29:24.723 --> 01:29:25.823
Right.

1311
01:29:29.186 --> 01:29:32.488
You know where.

1312
01:29:49.039 --> 01:29:52.550
You still have those cheap panties?

1313
01:29:52.730 --> 01:29:53.830
Huh?

1314
01:29:54.086 --> 01:29:56.846
The ones Yoon's girl left behind.

1315
01:29:57.965 --> 01:30:01.058
If you wear those.
fuck. it'll turn me on.

1316
01:30:01.593 --> 01:30:02.935
Really?

1317
01:30:03.470 --> 01:30:06.480
Then get me some drugs.

1318
01:30:07.057 --> 01:30:10.651
Get me some drugs!

1319
01:30:11.729 --> 01:30:13.195
Take this instead.

1320
01:30:25.242 --> 01:30:26.375
You like it?

1321
01:30:47.514 --> 01:30:49.899
- They're passed out cold.
- Sneak out now.

1322
01:31:23.967 --> 01:31:26.394
- Emergency!
- Emergency. over!

1323
01:31:28.931 --> 01:31:30.314
- Emergency!
- What?

1324
01:31:31.333 --> 01:31:32.333
What is it? Over!

1325
01:31:32.434 --> 01:31:34.002
Da-song. what's wrong?

1326
01:31:34.103 --> 01:31:36.570
I can't sleep. over.

1327
01:31:36.688 --> 01:31:40.591
So stop it and come in. okay?

1328
01:31:40.692 --> 01:31:43.344
Go sleep in your soft bed. over.

1329
01:31:43.445 --> 01:31:44.762
Right!

1330
01:31:44.863 --> 01:31:47.206
I don't want to. over.

1331
01:31:47.741 --> 01:31:49.166
Hey. Park Da-song.

1332
01:31:54.331 --> 01:31:56.674
Let's just sleep...

1333
01:33:31.427 --> 01:33:35.188
What happened back there?

1334
01:33:36.224 --> 01:33:37.324
What?

1335
01:33:39.644 --> 01:33:41.694
The people in the basement.

1336
01:33:44.357 --> 01:33:48.785
Well. I tied them up.

1337
01:33:49.237 --> 01:33:51.246
What will we do now?

1338
01:33:52.365 --> 01:33:53.540
Huh?

1339
01:33:56.077 --> 01:33:59.254
What do we do now.
what's our plan?

1340
01:33:59.872 --> 01:34:02.966
I've been wondering...

1341
01:34:03.709 --> 01:34:07.095
What would Min-hyuk do
in this situation?

1342
01:34:08.631 --> 01:34:10.974
Min-hyuk would never be
in this situation!

1343
01:34:13.010 --> 01:34:18.690
Look kids. we made it
out of there safely. right?

1344
01:34:19.767 --> 01:34:25.130
And besides us. nobody knows
what happened there. Right?

1345
01:34:25.231 --> 01:34:28.157
So nothing happened.
You understand?

1346
01:34:29.235 --> 01:34:33.830
I've got my own plan.

1347
01:34:34.365 --> 01:34:38.084
So you two just
forget about it. okay?

1348
01:34:38.619 --> 01:34:40.169
Let's go home.

1349
01:34:41.205 --> 01:34:43.256
Let's go and wash up. ok?

1350
01:35:01.892 --> 01:35:04.402
What are you doing there?
Hurry up!

1351
01:35:17.950 --> 01:35:20.209
What's going on?

1352
01:35:22.330 --> 01:35:25.065
You stay put!
This is all sewer water.

1353
01:35:25.166 --> 01:35:27.592
Our window was left open?

1354
01:35:32.131 --> 01:35:35.058
Help me out. Ki-taek!

1355
01:35:43.267 --> 01:35:44.692
Ki-woo!

1356
01:35:47.229 --> 01:35:50.198
Hey Ki-woo. close the window!

1357
01:35:51.233 --> 01:35:53.409
Did you get electrocuted?

1358
01:36:00.034 --> 01:36:01.751
I'm dizzy.

1359
01:36:05.331 --> 01:36:09.384
Hold still.

1360
01:36:14.924 --> 01:36:16.724
Shit. I feel dizzy.

1361
01:36:20.763 --> 01:36:23.314
Ki-Jung. be careful.

1362
01:36:24.850 --> 01:36:26.401
Don't touch anything.

1363
01:36:38.948 --> 01:36:44.602
Honey. I've got a concussion.

1364
01:36:44.703 --> 01:36:47.547
I can't see you.

1365
01:37:08.644 --> 01:37:13.406
Honey. that woman Chung-sook...

1366
01:37:13.941 --> 01:37:15.842
Oh. god.

1367
01:37:15.943 --> 01:37:18.286
What a nice person.

1368
01:37:19.864 --> 01:37:23.291
She kicked me down the stairs.

1369
01:37:25.828 --> 01:37:27.879
Repeat after me.

1370
01:37:28.414 --> 01:37:31.132
Chung-sook...

1371
01:37:32.668 --> 01:37:36.095
Chung-sook...

1372
01:37:45.014 --> 01:37:47.315
Hey. Ki-woo!

1373
01:37:48.100 --> 01:37:49.709
What at are you doing there?

1374
01:37:49.810 --> 01:37:50.910
Huh?

1375
01:38:05.910 --> 01:38:10.046
H. E. I. P. M...

1376
01:39:15.354 --> 01:39:16.571
Dad.

1377
01:39:17.231 --> 01:39:18.531
Yeah?

1378
01:39:19.567 --> 01:39:23.286
What's that plan of yours?

1379
01:39:24.863 --> 01:39:26.873
What are you talking about?

1380
01:39:27.908 --> 01:39:30.626
Earlier. you said you had a plan.

1381
01:39:31.161 --> 01:39:33.129
What are you going to do?
About...

1382
01:39:33.706 --> 01:39:34.963
the basement.

1383
01:39:35.999 --> 01:39:41.720
Ki-woo. you know what kind
of plan never fails?

1384
01:39:43.298 --> 01:39:45.824
A 'Non-Plan.'

1385
01:39:45.925 --> 01:39:47.601
No plan.

1386
01:39:48.136 --> 01:39:49.686
You know why?

1387
01:39:51.723 --> 01:39:58.403
If you make a plan.
life never turns out that way.

1388
01:39:58.938 --> 01:40:00.447
Look around us.

1389
01:40:00.982 --> 01:40:06.620
Did these people think.
"Let's spend the night in a gym?"

1390
01:40:07.155 --> 01:40:09.122
But look now.

1391
01:40:09.282 --> 01:40:13.293
Everyone's sleeping
on the floor. us included.

1392
01:40:14.829 --> 01:40:18.256
That's why people
shouldn't make plans.

1393
01:40:20.293 --> 01:40:24.071
With no plan.
nothing can go wrong.

1394
01:40:24.172 --> 01:40:31.061
And if something spins out
of control. it doesn't matter.

1395
01:40:32.096 --> 01:40:35.065
Whether you kill someone
or betray your country.

1396
01:40:36.601 --> 01:40:40.236
None of it fucking matters.
Got it?

1397
01:40:41.898 --> 01:40:43.365
Dad.

1398
01:40:45.401 --> 01:40:46.993
I'm sorry.

1399
01:40:47.612 --> 01:40:49.454
For what?

1400
01:40:52.492 --> 01:40:54.125
Everything.

1401
01:40:54.786 --> 01:40:56.586
All of it.

1402
01:40:58.623 --> 01:41:00.924
I'll take care of everything.

1403
01:41:01.459 --> 01:41:03.677
What are you talking about?

1404
01:41:05.713 --> 01:41:08.306
Why are you hugging that stone?

1405
01:41:08.925 --> 01:41:10.642
This?

1406
01:41:16.182 --> 01:41:19.317
It keeps clinging to me.

1407
01:41:21.354 --> 01:41:25.740
I think you need some sleep.

1408
01:41:28.778 --> 01:41:30.370
I'm serious.

1409
01:41:31.906 --> 01:41:34.499
It keeps following me.

1410
01:41:47.547 --> 01:41:49.483
Miss Jessica!
Sorry to call on a Sunday morning.

1411
01:41:49.507 --> 01:41:51.867
Are you free for lunch today?

1412
01:41:51.968 --> 01:41:55.729
We're having an impromptu
birthday for Da-song.

1413
01:41:57.306 --> 01:41:59.041
A birthday party?

1414
01:41:59.142 --> 01:42:02.569
If you come too.
Da-song will be so happy.

1415
01:42:02.770 --> 01:42:06.906
And have as much pasta. gratin.
and salmon steak as you want.

1416
01:42:07.024 --> 01:42:09.134
Please come by 1 pm.

1417
01:42:09.235 --> 01:42:12.346
and I'll count today as
one of your sessions.

1418
01:42:12.447 --> 01:42:14.998
You know what I mean?
See you soon!

1419
01:42:16.242 --> 01:42:17.684
- Mom.
- Yeah?

1420
01:42:17.785 --> 01:42:21.438
For the impromptu birthday.
should we invite teacher Kevin too?

1421
01:42:21.539 --> 01:42:24.316
Great idea! Why not?
Will you call him?

1422
01:42:24.417 --> 01:42:28.320
Get some more sleep. honey!
You must be tired after yesterday.

1423
01:42:28.421 --> 01:42:32.574
If we have a party.
won't you need to do the rounds?

1424
01:42:32.675 --> 01:42:37.062
Right. the wine shop.
supermarket. bakery. florist...

1425
01:42:37.889 --> 01:42:40.523
But I already told Mr. Kim
to hurry over.

1426
01:42:40.641 --> 01:42:42.334
I'll pay him overtime.

1427
01:42:42.435 --> 01:42:43.535
Perfect.

1428
01:42:54.071 --> 01:42:57.749
Everyone. calm down. calm down!

1429
01:42:57.992 --> 01:43:03.671
Da-hye: We're having a party.
and mom said to invite you!

1430
01:43:05.625 --> 01:43:08.944
In the basement...

1431
01:43:09.045 --> 01:43:11.321
we have ten outdoor tables.

1432
01:43:11.422 --> 01:43:15.308
First take them all out.
then arrange them...

1433
01:43:15.968 --> 01:43:19.187
No. come to the window.
I need to show you.

1434
01:43:20.890 --> 01:43:22.666
With Da-song's tent in the middle.

1435
01:43:22.767 --> 01:43:26.302
Set the tables outward in a curve...

1436
01:43:26.403 --> 01:43:28.547
A crane's wing formation!

1437
01:43:28.648 --> 01:43:31.933
Like Admiral Yi used. you know?
The Battle of Hansan Island!

1438
01:43:32.034 --> 01:43:34.594
Think of the tent as
the Japanese warship.

1439
01:43:34.695 --> 01:43:39.975
And our tables will make a
semicircular crane's wing formation.

1440
01:43:40.076 --> 01:43:44.271
Then near the tent will be the
barbeque grill. firewood and such.

1441
01:43:44.372 --> 01:43:46.573
All nicely arranged.

1442
01:43:46.674 --> 01:43:50.535
Bring your husband too!

1443
01:43:50.636 --> 01:43:51.361
Yeah!

1444
01:43:51.462 --> 01:43:55.431
And definitely no presents.
just come!

1445
01:43:56.300 --> 01:43:57.993
What dress code?

1446
01:43:58.094 --> 01:44:01.729
It's just an impromptu.
You can wear sweat pants!

1447
01:44:02.765 --> 01:44:08.528
And definitely no presents!
Just come and enjoy the food!

1448
01:44:09.564 --> 01:44:11.673
You know my culinary skills!

1449
01:44:11.774 --> 01:44:16.911
Right!
We'll get drunk in daylight.

1450
01:44:18.489 --> 01:44:22.000
If you'd sing. that'd be grand!
You know the one...

1451
01:44:38.050 --> 01:44:40.852
Quiet. he's sleeping!

1452
01:44:41.387 --> 01:44:44.456
Today the sky's so blue.
and no pollution!

1453
01:44:44.557 --> 01:44:46.733
Thanks to all the rain yesterday.

1454
01:44:47.768 --> 01:44:49.002
Right.

1455
01:44:49.103 --> 01:44:53.198
So we traded camping
for a garden party.

1456
01:44:54.233 --> 01:44:56.034
It's lemons into lemonade.

1457
01:44:59.155 --> 01:45:04.209
Right. that rain
was such a blessing!

1458
01:45:05.745 --> 01:45:10.256
And definitely no presents.
I mean it!

1459
01:45:10.791 --> 01:45:14.677
Right. just squeeze your
Mini Cooper into the garage.

1460
01:45:14.946 --> 01:45:15.946
Go on up!

1461
01:45:16.047 --> 01:45:20.959
Right. back it in.
Just don't block the Benz!

1462
01:45:21.060 --> 01:45:24.160
You're here! It's been so long!

1463
01:45:27.183 --> 01:45:29.525
I told you no presents!

1464
01:45:47.578 --> 01:45:49.712
You were thinking of
something else.

1465
01:45:49.872 --> 01:45:51.256
What?

1466
01:45:52.291 --> 01:45:55.468
While kissing me. you were
thinking of something else.

1467
01:45:57.588 --> 01:45:58.846
No.

1468
01:45:59.882 --> 01:46:03.518
What do you mean. no?
You're still doing it.

1469
01:46:06.055 --> 01:46:07.313
Wow.

1470
01:46:08.933 --> 01:46:11.651
Everyone looks gorgeous. right?

1471
01:46:13.062 --> 01:46:16.823
Even for an impromptu.
they all look so cool..

1472
01:46:17.692 --> 01:46:20.076
And so natural.

1473
01:46:22.113 --> 01:46:23.371
Da-hye.

1474
01:46:25.950 --> 01:46:27.583
Do I fit in here?

1475
01:46:28.961 --> 01:46:30.687
What?

1476
01:46:31.622 --> 01:46:34.632
In this setting. do I fit in?

1477
01:46:44.552 --> 01:46:46.769
Hey. where are you going?

1478
01:46:47.304 --> 01:46:48.521
I need to go down.

1479
01:46:49.056 --> 01:46:51.064
Just stay with me.

1480
01:46:52.058 --> 01:46:53.984
I need to go down there.

1481
01:46:54.394 --> 01:46:59.406
With all those boring people?
Can't you just hang out with me?

1482
01:47:00.400 --> 01:47:04.678
Not to those people. down lower.

1483
01:47:04.779 --> 01:47:07.706
Wow. what is that?

1484
01:47:10.744 --> 01:47:14.629
God. I can't believe
I'm doing this at my age.

1485
01:47:15.165 --> 01:47:17.132
It's embarrassing.

1486
01:47:18.168 --> 01:47:19.610
I'm really sorry. Mr. Kim.

1487
01:47:19.711 --> 01:47:22.905
It's at my wife's insistence.
I can't do anything about it.

1488
01:47:23.006 --> 01:47:24.573
But the concept is simple.

1489
01:47:24.674 --> 01:47:29.995
Jessica will carry out the
birthday cake in a little parade.

1490
01:47:30.096 --> 01:47:34.083
Then we jump out
and attack Jessica.

1491
01:47:34.184 --> 01:47:36.418
Swinging our tomahawks!

1492
01:47:36.519 --> 01:47:37.294
Right.

1493
01:47:37.395 --> 01:47:42.824
Just then. Da-song the good Indian
will jump out and we'll do battle.

1494
01:47:42.984 --> 01:47:47.554
Finally. he'll save Jessica.
the cake princess. and they'll all cheer.

1495
01:47:47.655 --> 01:47:49.247
Something like that.

1496
01:47:50.392 --> 01:47:51.392
Silly. isn't it?

1497
01:47:51.493 --> 01:47:56.313
I guess your wife likes
events and surprises.

1498
01:47:56.414 --> 01:47:58.507
Yeah. she does.

1499
01:47:58.666 --> 01:48:01.635
But she's particularly into this party.

1500
01:48:03.171 --> 01:48:06.139
You're trying your best. too.

1501
01:48:07.175 --> 01:48:10.143
Well. you love her. after all.

1502
01:48:15.683 --> 01:48:16.783
Mr. Kim.

1503
01:48:18.436 --> 01:48:21.071
You're getting paid extra.

1504
01:48:26.236 --> 01:48:30.580
Think of this as
part of your work. okay?

1505
01:48:41.876 --> 01:48:43.527
Have you been down there?

1506
01:48:43.628 --> 01:48:47.364
- Not yet.
- Shouldn't we talk to them?

1507
01:48:47.465 --> 01:48:49.283
Reach an understanding?

1508
01:48:49.384 --> 01:48:50.402
Exactly!

1509
01:48:50.426 --> 01:48:53.203
We all got too fucking
worked up last night.

1510
01:48:53.304 --> 01:48:57.232
Dad was going on
about some plan...

1511
01:48:57.642 --> 01:49:00.085
- I'm just going down there.
- Hold on.

1512
01:49:00.186 --> 01:49:02.379
Take this down to them.

1513
01:49:02.480 --> 01:49:04.089
- They must be hungry.
- Right.

1514
01:49:04.190 --> 01:49:06.158
Let them eat first.

1515
01:49:08.069 --> 01:49:09.703
Come next time for sure!

1516
01:49:10.738 --> 01:49:12.473
Here you are. Jessica.

1517
01:49:12.574 --> 01:49:14.933
- This is so amazing.
- Yes. to die for!

1518
01:49:15.034 --> 01:49:17.519
I've got a special favor to ask.

1519
01:49:17.620 --> 01:49:18.795
What kind?

1520
01:49:19.038 --> 01:49:21.106
This is... how to describe it?

1521
01:49:21.207 --> 01:49:23.150
Da-song's trauma recovery cake?

1522
01:49:23.251 --> 01:49:26.720
So it needs to be you who does it.
Today's highlight!

1523
01:50:49.671 --> 01:50:53.056
Hey. are you okay?

1524
01:50:58.096 --> 01:50:59.604
Are you...?

1525
01:51:09.649 --> 01:51:10.949
Wait. mister!

1526
01:52:57.965 --> 01:53:00.975
Kevin? Kevin!

1527
01:53:07.517 --> 01:53:10.252
Da-song. happy birthday!

1528
01:53:10.353 --> 01:53:11.820
Congratulations!

1529
01:53:19.073 --> 01:53:20.499
Shit...

1530
01:53:30.174 --> 01:53:32.274
Stop!

1531
01:53:32.375 --> 01:53:34.484
Chung-sook!

1532
01:53:34.585 --> 01:53:35.360
Ki-Jung!

1533
01:53:35.461 --> 01:53:37.070
Come out here. Chung-sook!

1534
01:53:37.171 --> 01:53:40.581
Stop the blood!
Push down on the wound!

1535
01:53:45.043 --> 01:53:46.478
Da-song!

1536
01:53:47.134 --> 01:53:48.353
Honey!

1537
01:53:49.535 --> 01:53:51.260
Let go. don't!

1538
01:54:02.611 --> 01:54:04.374
It hurts.

1539
01:54:08.871 --> 01:54:10.061
The emergency room!

1540
01:54:10.162 --> 01:54:11.695
Get the car!

1541
01:54:11.796 --> 01:54:13.339
Mr. Kim! What are you doing?

1542
01:54:13.440 --> 01:54:15.566
We can't wait for an ambulance!

1543
01:54:15.667 --> 01:54:18.077
Stop pushing. Dad!

1544
01:54:18.178 --> 01:54:21.138
Makes it hurt more.

1545
01:54:21.798 --> 01:54:22.948
Car keys! The car keys!

1546
01:54:23.049 --> 01:54:25.866
Throw them! Throw me the keys!

1547
01:54:43.486 --> 01:54:45.062
Are you okay?

1548
01:54:45.163 --> 01:54:47.164
Don't touch it!

1549
01:54:49.235 --> 01:54:51.752
How do you do. Mr. Park?

1550
01:54:51.870 --> 01:54:52.937
You know me?

1551
01:54:53.038 --> 01:54:54.713
Respect!

1552
01:56:21.376 --> 01:56:24.737
Opening my eyes for
the first time in a month.

1553
01:56:24.838 --> 01:56:26.638
I saw a detective.

1554
01:56:26.798 --> 01:56:31.577
You have the right
to an attorney...

1555
01:56:31.678 --> 01:56:33.979
He looked nothing
like a detective.

1556
01:56:38.518 --> 01:56:40.211
Is he laughing?

1557
01:56:40.312 --> 01:56:41.987
Just a sec.

1558
01:56:42.397 --> 01:56:47.242
Then the doctor. who looked
nothing like a doctor. spoke.

1559
01:56:48.278 --> 01:56:52.056
That happens sometimes
after brain surgery.

1560
01:56:52.157 --> 01:56:54.374
They keep laughing.
For no reason.

1561
01:56:55.035 --> 01:56:57.252
Do you hear me?

1562
01:56:57.495 --> 01:56:59.379
Can you hear me?

1563
01:56:59.497 --> 01:57:01.273
Then. we have to do it again?

1564
01:57:01.374 --> 01:57:02.291
Do what again?

1565
01:57:02.292 --> 01:57:03.842
The Miranda thing.

1566
01:57:06.379 --> 01:57:10.199
You have the right to remain silent.

1567
01:57:10.300 --> 01:57:13.035
Anything you say can and
will be used against you...

1568
01:57:13.136 --> 01:57:15.520
He keeps laughing. look!

1569
01:57:18.558 --> 01:57:24.655
Even when I heard how much
Ki-Jung bled that day...

1570
01:57:26.816 --> 01:57:34.031
Even when I heard the words forgery.
trespassing. foul play. self-defense

1571
01:57:34.282 --> 01:57:38.669
and that we were lucky to
get away with a probation...

1572
01:57:41.706 --> 01:57:44.733
Even when I finally
got to see Ki-jung's face...

1573
01:57:44.834 --> 01:57:47.844
Kim Ki-Jung.
Nov 20. 1996... July 1.2018.

1574
01:57:49.381 --> 01:57:51.682
I kept laughing.

1575
01:58:01.351 --> 01:58:06.839
Still. when I went back and
watched the news reports.

1576
01:58:06.940 --> 01:58:08.132
I didn't laugh.

1577
01:58:08.233 --> 01:58:12.303
This sudden rampage in the
back yard of an upper-class home

1578
01:58:12.404 --> 01:58:14.013
is a highly unusual case.

1579
01:58:14.114 --> 01:58:18.517
Since the homeless man who sparked
the rampage died at the scene.

1580
01:58:18.618 --> 01:58:23.981
police are struggling to even
establish a clear motive.

1581
01:58:24.082 --> 01:58:28.569
The suspect Kim and the slain Mr. Park
are said to have been on good terms.

1582
01:58:28.670 --> 01:58:34.182
For now the police investigation is
focused on locating the driver. Kim.

1583
01:58:34.717 --> 01:58:38.454
Kim. after exiting this door
and descending the stairs.

1584
01:58:38.555 --> 01:58:42.065
disappeared into the
neighboring alleys.

1585
01:58:42.600 --> 01:58:47.738
Police searched the CCTVs
of nearby homes to no avail.

1586
01:58:48.273 --> 01:58:51.408
and they have yet
to find any witnesses.

1587
01:58:51.943 --> 01:58:54.011
Given the situation.

1588
01:58:54.112 --> 01:58:59.374
it's not an exaggeration to say
that Kim has vanished into thin air.

1589
01:59:00.493 --> 01:59:07.458
Actually Mom and I had
no idea where Dad was.

1590
01:59:09.794 --> 01:59:15.474
But those detectives still
wore themselves out tailing us.

1591
01:59:19.512 --> 01:59:25.484
Eventually the news went quiet.
and after the tails stopped...

1592
01:59:26.019 --> 01:59:29.446
I started going up that mountain.

1593
01:59:31.483 --> 01:59:36.203
From up there. you get
a good view of the house.

1594
01:59:38.948 --> 01:59:46.079
That day. despite the cold.
I felt like staying longer.

1595
01:59:59.427 --> 02:00:02.938
Dash - dash - dot - dot.

1596
02:00:27.997 --> 02:00:29.381
Son!

1597
02:00:31.417 --> 02:00:32.759
Son!

1598
02:00:34.796 --> 02:00:38.640
You may be able to
read this letter.

1599
02:00:42.178 --> 02:00:48.483
You were a Boy Scout.
so I'm writing this just in case.

1600
02:00:51.521 --> 02:00:54.489
Have you recovered from
your injuries?

1601
02:00:55.525 --> 02:00:59.828
I'm sure your mom
is plenty healthy.

1602
02:01:03.866 --> 02:01:06.668
I'm doing fine down here.

1603
02:01:07.704 --> 02:01:10.463
Though. I often cry
thinking about Ki-Jung.

1604
02:01:13.501 --> 02:01:18.346
Even now. what happened
that day seems surreal.

1605
02:01:19.591 --> 02:01:21.307
It feels like a dream.

1606
02:01:22.843 --> 02:01:24.810
and yet it doesn't.

1607
02:01:25.846 --> 02:01:30.816
That day. as I ran out the gate.
I suddenly realized

1608
02:01:31.852 --> 02:01:33.611
where I needed to go.

1609
02:02:13.018 --> 02:02:16.003
A house where such
grisly crime took place

1610
02:02:16.104 --> 02:02:19.365
would surely not
be easy to sell.

1611
02:02:22.486 --> 02:02:24.887
I'm sorry. Mr. Park.

1612
02:02:24.988 --> 02:02:31.543
I struggled to hold out
like that in an empty house.

1613
02:02:34.081 --> 02:02:36.983
Still. thanks to
the house being empty.

1614
02:02:37.084 --> 02:02:41.946
What was her name? Moon-gwang?

1615
02:02:42.047 --> 02:02:46.350
I was able to give her
a dignified send off.

1616
02:02:47.469 --> 02:02:54.233
I hear tree-side burials are trendy.
So hell. I did my best.

1617
02:02:57.771 --> 02:03:01.407
But those real estate sharks
sure are clever.

1618
02:03:05.946 --> 02:03:10.182
They hoodwinked some people
who had just arrived in Korea

1619
02:03:10.283 --> 02:03:12.626
and managed to sell the house.

1620
02:03:13.745 --> 02:03:17.023
With the parents working.
and the kids attending school.

1621
02:03:17.124 --> 02:03:19.717
the family is usually out.

1622
02:03:19.835 --> 02:03:25.264
But the goddamned housekeeper
stays glued here 24 hours a day.

1623
02:03:25.424 --> 02:03:30.352
Each time I go upstairs.
I put my life on the line.

1624
02:03:32.889 --> 02:03:37.234
It turns out Germans eat more
than just sausage and beer.

1625
02:03:37.769 --> 02:03:39.820
What a relief.

1626
02:03:42.399 --> 02:03:46.785
Passing the time down here.
everything starts to go hazy.

1627
02:03:51.324 --> 02:03:55.502
Today at least
I was able to write you a letter.

1628
02:03:57.038 --> 02:04:00.941
If I send out the letter
this way every night.

1629
02:04:01.042 --> 02:04:05.512
maybe someday you'll see it.

1630
02:04:11.553 --> 02:04:13.604
So long for now.

1631
02:04:27.152 --> 02:04:28.219
Ki-woo? Is that you?

1632
02:04:28.320 --> 02:04:29.420
Yes.

1633
02:04:43.835 --> 02:04:48.847
Dad. I made a plan today.

1634
02:04:50.383 --> 02:04:52.309
It's a master plan.

1635
02:04:55.347 --> 02:04:57.022
I'm going to make money.

1636
02:04:57.599 --> 02:04:59.399
Loads of it.

1637
02:05:02.938 --> 02:05:07.449
University. a career. marriage.
Those are all fine.

1638
02:05:07.609 --> 02:05:09.635
but first I'll make money.

1639
02:05:09.736 --> 02:05:15.082
You'll see once you go in.
but it's very spacious.

1640
02:05:15.617 --> 02:05:20.354
Actually. we don't show
this house to just anyone.

1641
02:05:20.455 --> 02:05:24.967
When I have money.
I'll buy that house.

1642
02:05:26.002 --> 02:05:30.264
On the day we move in.
Mom and I will be in the garden.

1643
02:05:30.799 --> 02:05:33.225
Because the sunshine
is so nice there.

1644
02:05:34.386 --> 02:05:36.436
All you have to do

1645
02:05:36.596 --> 02:05:39.481
is come up the stairs.

1646
02:07:02.098 --> 02:07:06.235
Until then. take good
care of yourself.

1647
02:07:10.899 --> 02:07:13.033
So long!

1647
02:07:14.305 --> 02:08:14.168
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
